        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><table>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000016\">Introduction</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000030\">Chapter I. The Cyclone</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000073\">Chapter II. The Council with the Munchkins</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000192\">Chapter III. How Dorothy Saved the Scarecrow</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000307\">Chapter IV. The Road Through the Forest</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000384\">Chapter V. The Rescue of the Tin Woodman</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000491\">Chapter VI. The Cowardly Lion</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000588\">Chapter VII. The Journey to the Great Oz</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000673\">Chapter VIII. The Deadly Poppy Field</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000788\">Chapter IX. The Queen of the Field Mice</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000873\">Chapter X. The Guardian of the Gates</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000990\">Chapter XI. The Emerald City of Oz</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001195\">Chapter XII. The Search for the Wicked Witch</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001364\">Chapter XIII. The Rescue</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001425\">Chapter XIV. The Winged Monkeys</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001514\">Chapter XV. The Discovery of Oz, the Terrible</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001701\">Chapter XVI. The Magic Art of the Great Humbug</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001786\">Chapter XVII. How the Balloon Was Launched</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001855\">Chapter XVIII. Away to the South</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001952\">Chapter XIX. Attacked by the Fighting Trees</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002009\">Chapter XX. The Dainty China Country</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002102\">Chapter XXI. The Lion Becomes the King of Beasts</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002155\">Chapter XXII. The Country of the Quadlings</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002216\">Chapter XXIII. Glinda The Good Witch Grants Dorothy’s Wish</$link></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002299\">Chapter XXIV. Home Again</$link></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Introduction</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Folklore, legends, myths and fairy tales have followed childhood through the ages, for every healthy youngster has a wholesome and instinctive love for stories fantastic, marvelous and manifestly unreal. The winged fairies of Grimm and Andersen have brought more happiness to childish hearts than all other human creations.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Yet the old time fairy tale, having served for generations, may now be classed as “historical” in the children’s library; for the time has come for a series of newer “wonder tales” in which the stereotyped genie, dwarf and fairy are eliminated, together with all the horrible and blood-curdling incidents devised by their authors to point a fearsome moral to each tale. Modern education includes morality; therefore the modern child seeks only entertainment in its wonder tales and gladly dispenses with all disagreeable incident.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Having this thought in mind, the story of “The Wonderful Wizard of Oz” was written solely to please children of today. It aspires to being a modernized fairy tale, in which the wonderment and joy are retained and the heartaches and nightmares are left out.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000024",
