        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter I<br>\nThe Cyclone</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy lived in the midst of the great Kansas prairies, with Uncle Henry, who was a farmer, and Aunt Em, who was the farmer’s wife. Their house was small, for the lumber to build it had to be carried by wagon many miles. There were four walls, a floor and a roof, which made one room; and this room contained a rusty looking cookstove, a cupboard for the dishes, a table, three or four chairs, and the beds. Uncle Henry and Aunt Em had a big bed in one corner, and Dorothy a little bed in another corner. There was no garret at all, and no cellar—except a small hole dug in the ground, called a cyclone cellar, where the family could go in case one of those great whirlwinds arose, mighty enough to crush any building in its path. It was reached by a trap door in the middle of the floor, from which a ladder led down into the small, dark hole.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When Dorothy stood in the doorway and looked around, she could see nothing but the great gray prairie on every side. Not a tree nor a house broke the broad sweep of flat country that reached to the edge of the sky in all directions. The sun had baked the plowed land into a gray mass, with little cracks running through it. Even the grass was not green, for the sun had burned the tops of the long blades until they were the same gray color to be seen everywhere. Once the house had been painted, but the sun blistered the paint and the rains washed it away, and now the house was as dull and gray as everything else.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When Aunt Em came there to live she was a young, pretty wife. The sun and wind had changed her, too. They had taken the sparkle from her eyes and left them a sober gray; they had taken the red from her cheeks and lips, and they were gray also. She was thin and gaunt, and never smiled now. When Dorothy, who was an orphan, first came to her, Aunt Em had been so startled by the child’s laughter that she would scream and press her hand upon her heart whenever Dorothy’s merry voice reached her ears; and she still looked at the little girl with wonder that she could find anything to laugh at.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Uncle Henry never laughed. He worked hard from morning till night and did not know what joy was. He was gray also, from his long beard to his rough boots, and he looked stern and solemn, and rarely spoke.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>It was Toto that made Dorothy laugh, and saved her from growing as gray as her other surroundings. Toto was not gray; he was a little black dog, with long silky hair and small black eyes that twinkled merrily on either side of his funny, wee nose. Toto played all day long, and Dorothy played with him, and loved him dearly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Today, however, they were not playing. Uncle Henry sat upon the doorstep and looked anxiously at the sky, which was even grayer than usual. Dorothy stood in the door with Toto in her arms, and looked at the sky too. Aunt Em was washing the dishes.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000043": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000043",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000044": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000044",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>From the far north they heard a low wail of the wind, and Uncle Henry and Dorothy could see where the long grass bowed in waves before the coming storm. There now came a sharp whistling in the air from the south, and as they turned their eyes that way they saw ripples in the grass coming from that direction also.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000045": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000045",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000046": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000046",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Suddenly Uncle Henry stood up.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000047": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000047",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000048": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000048",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“There’s a cyclone coming, Em,” he called to his wife. “I’ll go look after the stock.” Then he ran toward the sheds where the cows and horses were kept.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000049": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000049",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000050": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000050",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Aunt Em dropped her work and came to the door. One glance told her of the danger close at hand.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000051": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000051",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000052": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000052",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Quick, Dorothy!” she screamed. “Run for the cellar!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000053": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000053",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000054": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000054",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Toto jumped out of Dorothy’s arms and hid under the bed, and the girl started to get him. Aunt Em, badly frightened, threw open the trap door in the floor and climbed down the ladder into the small, dark hole. Dorothy caught Toto at last and started to follow her aunt. When she was halfway across the room there came a great shriek from the wind, and the house shook so hard that she lost her footing and sat down suddenly upon the floor.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000055": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000055",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000056": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000056",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then a strange thing happened.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000057": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000057",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000058": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000058",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The house whirled around two or three times and rose slowly through the air. Dorothy felt as if she were going up in a balloon.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000059": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000059",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000060": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000060",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The north and south winds met where the house stood, and made it the exact center of the cyclone. In the middle of a cyclone the air is generally still, but the great pressure of the wind on every side of the house raised it up higher and higher, until it was at the very top of the cyclone; and there it remained and was carried miles and miles away as easily as you could carry a feather.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000061": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000061",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000062": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000062",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>It was very dark, and the wind howled horribly around her, but Dorothy found she was riding quite easily. After the first few whirls around, and one other time when the house tipped badly, she felt as if she were being rocked gently, like a baby in a cradle.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000063": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000063",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000064": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000064",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Toto did not like it. He ran about the room, now here, now there, barking loudly; but Dorothy sat quite still on the floor and waited to see what would happen.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000065": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000065",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000066": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000066",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Once Toto got too near the open trap door, and fell in; and at first the little girl thought she had lost him. But soon she saw one of his ears sticking up through the hole, for the strong pressure of the air was keeping him up so that he could not fall. She crept to the hole, caught Toto by the ear, and dragged him into the room again, afterward closing the trap door so that no more accidents could happen.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000067": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000067",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000068": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000068",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Hour after hour passed away, and slowly Dorothy got over her fright; but she felt quite lonely, and the wind shrieked so loudly all about her that she nearly became deaf. At first she had wondered if she would be dashed to pieces when the house fell again; but as the hours passed and nothing terrible happened, she stopped worrying and resolved to wait calmly and see what the future would bring. At last she crawled over the swaying floor to her bed, and lay down upon it; and Toto followed and lay down beside her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000069": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000069",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000070": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000070",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>In spite of the swaying of the house and the wailing of the wind, Dorothy soon closed her eyes and fell fast asleep.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000071": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000071",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000072": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000072",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000073": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000073",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter II<br>\nThe Council with the Munchkins</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000074": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000074",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000075": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000075",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She was awakened by a shock, so sudden and severe that if Dorothy had not been lying on the soft bed she might have been hurt. As it was, the jar made her catch her breath and wonder what had happened; and Toto put his cold little nose into her face and whined dismally. Dorothy sat up and noticed that the house was not moving; nor was it dark, for the bright sunshine came in at the window, flooding the little room. She sprang from her bed and with Toto at her heels ran and opened the door.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000076": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000076",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000077": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000077",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The little girl gave a cry of amazement and looked about her, her eyes growing bigger and bigger at the wonderful sights she saw.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000078": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000078",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000079": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000079",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The cyclone had set the house down very gently—for a cyclone—in the midst of a country of marvelous beauty. There were lovely patches of greensward all about, with stately trees bearing rich and luscious fruits. Banks of gorgeous flowers were on every hand, and birds with rare and brilliant plumage sang and fluttered in the trees and bushes. A little way off was a small brook, rushing and sparkling along between green banks, and murmuring in a voice very grateful to a little girl who had lived so long on the dry, gray prairies.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000080": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000080",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000081": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000081",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>While she stood looking eagerly at the strange and beautiful sights, she noticed coming toward her a group of the queerest people she had ever seen. They were not as big as the grown folk she had always been used to; but neither were they very small. In fact, they seemed about as tall as Dorothy, who was a well-grown child for her age, although they were, so far as looks go, many years older.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000082": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000082",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000083": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000083",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Three were men and one a woman, and all were oddly dressed. They wore round hats that rose to a small point a foot above their heads, with little bells around the brims that tinkled sweetly as they moved. The hats of the men were blue; the little woman’s hat was white, and she wore a white gown that hung in pleats from her shoulders. Over it were sprinkled little stars that glistened in the sun like diamonds. The men were dressed in blue, of the same shade as their hats, and wore well-polished boots with a deep roll of blue at the tops. The men, Dorothy thought, were about as old as Uncle Henry, for two of them had beards. But the little woman was doubtless much older. Her face was covered with wrinkles, her hair was nearly white, and she walked rather stiffly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000084": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000084",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000085": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000085",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When these people drew near the house where Dorothy was standing in the doorway, they paused and whispered among themselves, as if afraid to come farther. But the little old woman walked up to Dorothy, made a low bow and said, in a sweet voice:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000086": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000086",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000087": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000087",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You are welcome, most noble Sorceress, to the land of the Munchkins. We are so grateful to you for having killed the Wicked Witch of the East, and for setting our people free from bondage.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000088": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000088",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000089": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000089",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy listened to this speech with wonder. What could the little woman possibly mean by calling her a sorceress, and saying she had killed the Wicked Witch of the East? Dorothy was an innocent, harmless little girl, who had been carried by a cyclone many miles from home; and she had never killed anything in all her life.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000090": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000090",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000091": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000091",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the little woman evidently expected her to answer; so Dorothy said, with hesitation, “You are very kind, but there must be some mistake. I have not killed anything.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000092": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000092",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000093": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000093",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Your house did, anyway,” replied the little old woman, with a laugh, “and that is the same thing. See!” she continued, pointing to the corner of the house. “There are her two feet, still sticking out from under a block of wood.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000094": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000094",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000095": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000095",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy looked, and gave a little cry of fright. There, indeed, just under the corner of the great beam the house rested on, two feet were sticking out, shod in silver shoes with pointed toes.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000096": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000096",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000097": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000097",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, dear! Oh, dear!” cried Dorothy, clasping her hands together in dismay. “The house must have fallen on her. Whatever shall we do?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000098": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000098",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000099": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000099",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“There is nothing to be done,” said the little woman calmly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000100": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000100",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000101": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000101",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But who was she?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000102": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000102",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000103": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000103",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“She was the Wicked Witch of the East, as I said,” answered the little woman. “She has held all the Munchkins in bondage for many years, making them slave for her night and day. Now they are all set free, and are grateful to you for the favor.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000104": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000104",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000105": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000105",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Who are the Munchkins?” inquired Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000106": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000106",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000107": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000107",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“They are the people who live in this land of the East where the Wicked Witch ruled.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000108": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000108",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000109": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000109",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Are you a Munchkin?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000110": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000110",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000111": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000111",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No, but I am their friend, although I live in the land of the North. When they saw the Witch of the East was dead the Munchkins sent a swift messenger to me, and I came at once. I am the Witch of the North.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000112": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000112",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000113": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000113",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, gracious!” cried Dorothy. “Are you a real witch?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000114": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000114",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000115": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000115",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yes, indeed,” answered the little woman. “But I am a good witch, and the people love me. I am not as powerful as the Wicked Witch was who ruled here, or I should have set the people free myself.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000116": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000116",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000117": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000117",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But I thought all witches were wicked,” said the girl, who was half frightened at facing a real witch. “Oh, no, that is a great mistake. There were only four witches in all the Land of Oz, and two of them, those who live in the North and the South, are good witches. I know this is true, for I am one of them myself, and cannot be mistaken. Those who dwelt in the East and the West were, indeed, wicked witches; but now that you have killed one of them, there is but one Wicked Witch in all the Land of Oz—the one who lives in the West.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000118": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000118",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000119": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000119",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But,” said Dorothy, after a moment’s thought, “Aunt Em has told me that the witches were all dead—years and years ago.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000120": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000120",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000121": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000121",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Who is Aunt Em?” inquired the little old woman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000122": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000122",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000123": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000123",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“She is my aunt who lives in Kansas, where I came from.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000124": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000124",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000125": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000125",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Witch of the North seemed to think for a time, with her head bowed and her eyes upon the ground. Then she looked up and said, “I do not know where Kansas is, for I have never heard that country mentioned before. But tell me, is it a civilized country?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000126": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000126",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000127": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000127",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, yes,” replied Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000128": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000128",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000129": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000129",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Then that accounts for it. In the civilized countries I believe there are no witches left, nor wizards, nor sorceresses, nor magicians. But, you see, the Land of Oz has never been civilized, for we are cut off from all the rest of the world. Therefore we still have witches and wizards amongst us.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000130": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000130",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000131": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000131",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Who are the wizards?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000132": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000132",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000133": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000133",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oz himself is the Great Wizard,” answered the Witch, sinking her voice to a whisper. “He is more powerful than all the rest of us together. He lives in the City of Emeralds.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000134": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000134",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000135": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000135",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy was going to ask another question, but just then the Munchkins, who had been standing silently by, gave a loud shout and pointed to the corner of the house where the Wicked Witch had been lying.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000136": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000136",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000137": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000137",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What is it?” asked the little old woman, and looked, and began to laugh. The feet of the dead Witch had disappeared entirely, and nothing was left but the silver shoes.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000138": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000138",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000139": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000139",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“She was so old,” explained the Witch of the North, “that she dried up quickly in the sun. That is the end of her. But the silver shoes are yours, and you shall have them to wear.” She reached down and picked up the shoes, and after shaking the dust out of them handed them to Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000140": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000140",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000141": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000141",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The Witch of the East was proud of those silver shoes,” said one of the Munchkins, “and there is some charm connected with them; but what it is we never knew.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000142": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000142",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000143": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000143",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy carried the shoes into the house and placed them on the table. Then she came out again to the Munchkins and said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000144": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000144",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000145": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000145",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am anxious to get back to my aunt and uncle, for I am sure they will worry about me. Can you help me find my way?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000146": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000146",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000147": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000147",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Munchkins and the Witch first looked at one another, and then at Dorothy, and then shook their heads.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000148": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000148",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000149": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000149",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“At the East, not far from here,” said one, “there is a great desert, and none could live to cross it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000150": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000150",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000151": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000151",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It is the same at the South,” said another, “for I have been there and seen it. The South is the country of the Quadlings.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000152": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000152",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000153": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000153",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am told,” said the third man, “that it is the same at the West. And that country, where the Winkies live, is ruled by the Wicked Witch of the West, who would make you her slave if you passed her way.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000154": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000154",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000155": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000155",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The North is my home,” said the old lady, “and at its edge is the same great desert that surrounds this Land of Oz. I’m afraid, my dear, you will have to live with us.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000156": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000156",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000157": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000157",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy began to sob at this, for she felt lonely among all these strange people. Her tears seemed to grieve the kind-hearted Munchkins, for they immediately took out their handkerchiefs and began to weep also. As for the little old woman, she took off her cap and balanced the point on the end of her nose, while she counted “One, two, three” in a solemn voice. At once the cap changed to a slate, on which was written in big, white chalk marks:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p class=\"center\">“LET DOROTHY GO TO THE CITY OF EMERALDS”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The little old woman took the slate from her nose, and having read the words on it, asked, “Is your name Dorothy, my dear?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yes,” answered the child, looking up and drying her tears.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000165",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Then you must go to the City of Emeralds. Perhaps Oz will help you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000166": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000166",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000167": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000167",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Where is this city?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000168": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000168",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000169": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000169",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It is exactly in the center of the country, and is ruled by Oz, the Great Wizard I told you of.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000170": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000170",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000171": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000171",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Is he a good man?” inquired the girl anxiously.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000172": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000172",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000173": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000173",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“He is a good Wizard. Whether he is a man or not I cannot tell, for I have never seen him.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000174": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000174",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000175": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000175",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How can I get there?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000176": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000176",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000177": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000177",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You must walk. It is a long journey, through a country that is sometimes pleasant and sometimes dark and terrible. However, I will use all the magic arts I know of to keep you from harm.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000178": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000178",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000179": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000179",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Won’t you go with me?” pleaded the girl, who had begun to look upon the little old woman as her only friend.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000180": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000180",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000181": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000181",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No, I cannot do that,” she replied, “but I will give you my kiss, and no one will dare injure a person who has been kissed by the Witch of the North.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000182": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000182",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000183": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000183",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She came close to Dorothy and kissed her gently on the forehead. Where her lips touched the girl they left a round, shining mark, as Dorothy found out soon after.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000184": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000184",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000185": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000185",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The road to the City of Emeralds is paved with yellow brick,” said the Witch, “so you cannot miss it. When you get to Oz do not be afraid of him, but tell your story and ask him to help you. Good-bye, my dear.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000186": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000186",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000187": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000187",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The three Munchkins bowed low to her and wished her a pleasant journey, after which they walked away through the trees. The Witch gave Dorothy a friendly little nod, whirled around on her left heel three times, and straightway disappeared, much to the surprise of little Toto, who barked after her loudly enough when she had gone, because he had been afraid even to growl while she stood by.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000188": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000188",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000189": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000189",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But Dorothy, knowing her to be a witch, had expected her to disappear in just that way, and was not surprised in the least.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000190": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000190",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000191": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000191",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000192": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000192",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter III<br>\nHow Dorothy Saved the Scarecrow</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000193": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000193",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000194": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000194",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When Dorothy was left alone she began to feel hungry. So she went to the cupboard and cut herself some bread, which she spread with butter. She gave some to Toto, and taking a pail from the shelf she carried it down to the little brook and filled it with clear, sparkling water. Toto ran over to the trees and began to bark at the birds sitting there. Dorothy went to get him, and saw such delicious fruit hanging from the branches that she gathered some of it, finding it just what she wanted to help out her breakfast.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000195": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000195",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000196": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000196",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then she went back to the house, and having helped herself and Toto to a good drink of the cool, clear water, she set about making ready for the journey to the City of Emeralds.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000197": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000197",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000198": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000198",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy had only one other dress, but that happened to be clean and was hanging on a peg beside her bed. It was gingham, with checks of white and blue; and although the blue was somewhat faded with many washings, it was still a pretty frock. The girl washed herself carefully, dressed herself in the clean gingham, and tied her pink sunbonnet on her head. She took a little basket and filled it with bread from the cupboard, laying a white cloth over the top. Then she looked down at her feet and noticed how old and worn her shoes were.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000199": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000199",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000200": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000200",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“They surely will never do for a long journey, Toto,” she said. And Toto looked up into her face with his little black eyes and wagged his tail to show he knew what she meant.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000201": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000201",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000202": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000202",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>At that moment Dorothy saw lying on the table the silver shoes that had belonged to the Witch of the East.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000203": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000203",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000204": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000204",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I wonder if they will fit me,” she said to Toto. “They would be just the thing to take a long walk in, for they could not wear out.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000205": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000205",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000206": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000206",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She took off her old leather shoes and tried on the silver ones, which fitted her as well as if they had been made for her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000207": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000207",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000208": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000208",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Finally she picked up her basket.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000209": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000209",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000210": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000210",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come along, Toto,” she said. “We will go to the Emerald City and ask the Great Oz how to get back to Kansas again.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000211": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000211",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000212": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000212",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She closed the door, locked it, and put the key carefully in the pocket of her dress. And so, with Toto trotting along soberly behind her, she started on her journey.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000213": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000213",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000214": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000214",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>There were several roads nearby, but it did not take her long to find the one paved with yellow bricks. Within a short time she was walking briskly toward the Emerald City, her silver shoes tinkling merrily on the hard, yellow road-bed. The sun shone bright and the birds sang sweetly, and Dorothy did not feel nearly so bad as you might think a little girl would who had been suddenly whisked away from her own country and set down in the midst of a strange land.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000215": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000215",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000216": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000216",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She was surprised, as she walked along, to see how pretty the country was about her. There were neat fences at the sides of the road, painted a dainty blue color, and beyond them were fields of grain and vegetables in abundance. Evidently the Munchkins were good farmers and able to raise large crops. Once in a while she would pass a house, and the people came out to look at her and bow low as she went by; for everyone knew she had been the means of destroying the Wicked Witch and setting them free from bondage. The houses of the Munchkins were odd-looking dwellings, for each was round, with a big dome for a roof. All were painted blue, for in this country of the East blue was the favorite color.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000217": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000217",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000218": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000218",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Toward evening, when Dorothy was tired with her long walk and began to wonder where she should pass the night, she came to a house rather larger than the rest. On the green lawn before it many men and women were dancing. Five little fiddlers played as loudly as possible, and the people were laughing and singing, while a big table near by was loaded with delicious fruits and nuts, pies and cakes, and many other good things to eat.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000219": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000219",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000220": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000220",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The people greeted Dorothy kindly, and invited her to supper and to pass the night with them; for this was the home of one of the richest Munchkins in the land, and his friends were gathered with him to celebrate their freedom from the bondage of the Wicked Witch.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000221": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000221",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000222": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000222",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy ate a hearty supper and was waited upon by the rich Munchkin himself, whose name was Boq. Then she sat upon a settee and watched the people dance.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000223": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000223",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000224": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000224",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When Boq saw her silver shoes he said, “You must be a great sorceress.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000225": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000225",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000226": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000226",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why?” asked the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000227": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000227",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Because you wear silver shoes and have killed the Wicked Witch. Besides, you have white in your frock, and only witches and sorceresses wear white.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My dress is blue and white checked,” said Dorothy, smoothing out the wrinkles in it.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It is kind of you to wear that,” said Boq. “Blue is the color of the Munchkins, and white is the witch color. So we know you are a friendly witch.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy did not know what to say to this, for all the people seemed to think her a witch, and she knew very well she was only an ordinary little girl who had come by the chance of a cyclone into a strange land.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When she had tired watching the dancing, Boq led her into the house, where he gave her a room with a pretty bed in it. The sheets were made of blue cloth, and Dorothy slept soundly in them till morning, with Toto curled up on the blue rug beside her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She ate a hearty breakfast, and watched a wee Munchkin baby, who played with Toto and pulled his tail and crowed and laughed in a way that greatly amused Dorothy. Toto was a fine curiosity to all the people, for they had never seen a dog before.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How far is it to the Emerald City?” the girl asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I do not know,” answered Boq gravely, “for I have never been there. It is better for people to keep away from Oz, unless they have business with him. But it is a long way to the Emerald City, and it will take you many days. The country here is rich and pleasant, but you must pass through rough and dangerous places before you reach the end of your journey.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>This worried Dorothy a little, but she knew that only the Great Oz could help her get to Kansas again, so she bravely resolved not to turn back.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She bade her friends good-bye, and again started along the road of yellow brick. When she had gone several miles she thought she would stop to rest, and so climbed to the top of the fence beside the road and sat down. There was a great cornfield beyond the fence, and not far away she saw a Scarecrow, placed high on a pole to keep the birds from the ripe corn.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy leaned her chin upon her hand and gazed thoughtfully at the Scarecrow. Its head was a small sack stuffed with straw, with eyes, nose, and mouth painted on it to represent a face. An old, pointed blue hat, that had belonged to some Munchkin, was perched on his head, and the rest of the figure was a blue suit of clothes, worn and faded, which had also been stuffed with straw. On the feet were some old boots with blue tops, such as every man wore in this country, and the figure was raised above the stalks of corn by means of the pole stuck up its back.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>While Dorothy was looking earnestly into the queer, painted face of the Scarecrow, she was surprised to see one of the eyes slowly wink at her. She thought she must have been mistaken at first, for none of the scarecrows in Kansas ever wink; but presently the figure nodded its head to her in a friendly way. Then she climbed down from the fence and walked up to it, while Toto ran around the pole and barked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Good day,” said the Scarecrow, in a rather husky voice.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Did you speak?” asked the girl, in wonder.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Certainly,” answered the Scarecrow. “How do you do?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I’m pretty well, thank you,” replied Dorothy politely. “How do you do?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I’m not feeling well,” said the Scarecrow, with a smile, “for it is very tedious being perched up here night and day to scare away crows.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Can’t you get down?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No, for this pole is stuck up my back. If you will please take away the pole I shall be greatly obliged to you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy reached up both arms and lifted the figure off the pole, for, being stuffed with straw, it was quite light.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Thank you very much,” said the Scarecrow, when he had been set down on the ground. “I feel like a new man.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy was puzzled at this, for it sounded queer to hear a stuffed man speak, and to see him bow and walk along beside her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Who are you?” asked the Scarecrow when he had stretched himself and yawned. “And where are you going?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My name is Dorothy,” said the girl, “and I am going to the Emerald City, to ask the Great Oz to send me back to Kansas.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Where is the Emerald City?” he inquired. “And who is Oz?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why, don’t you know?” she returned, in surprise.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No, indeed. I don’t know anything. You see, I am stuffed, so I have no brains at all,” he answered sadly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh,” said Dorothy, “I’m awfully sorry for you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Do you think,” he asked, “if I go to the Emerald City with you, that Oz would give me some brains?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I cannot tell,” she returned, “but you may come with me, if you like. If Oz will not give you any brains you will be no worse off than you are now.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is true,” said the Scarecrow. “You see,” he continued confidentially, “I don’t mind my legs and arms and body being stuffed, because I cannot get hurt. If anyone treads on my toes or sticks a pin into me, it doesn’t matter, for I can’t feel it. But I do not want people to call me a fool, and if my head stays stuffed with straw instead of with brains, as yours is, how am I ever to know anything?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I understand how you feel,” said the little girl, who was truly sorry for him. “If you will come with me I’ll ask Oz to do all he can for you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Thank you,” he answered gratefully.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They walked back to the road. Dorothy helped him over the fence, and they started along the path of yellow brick for the Emerald City.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Toto did not like this addition to the party at first. He smelled around the stuffed man as if he suspected there might be a nest of rats in the straw, and he often growled in an unfriendly way at the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Don’t mind Toto,” said Dorothy to her new friend. “He never bites.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, I’m not afraid,” replied the Scarecrow. “He can’t hurt the straw. Do let me carry that basket for you. I shall not mind it, for I can’t get tired. I’ll tell you a secret,” he continued, as he walked along. “There is only one thing in the world I am afraid of.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What is that?” asked Dorothy; “the Munchkin farmer who made you?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No,” answered the Scarecrow; “it’s a lighted match.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000307": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000307",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter IV<br>\nThe Road Through the Forest</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000308": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000308",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>After a few hours the road began to be rough, and the walking grew so difficult that the Scarecrow often stumbled over the yellow bricks, which were here very uneven. Sometimes, indeed, they were broken or missing altogether, leaving holes that Toto jumped across and Dorothy walked around. As for the Scarecrow, having no brains, he walked straight ahead, and so stepped into the holes and fell at full length on the hard bricks. It never hurt him, however, and Dorothy would pick him up and set him upon his feet again, while he joined her in laughing merrily at his own mishap.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The farms were not nearly so well cared for here as they were farther back. There were fewer houses and fewer fruit trees, and the farther they went the more dismal and lonesome the country became.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>At noon they sat down by the roadside, near a little brook, and Dorothy opened her basket and got out some bread. She offered a piece to the Scarecrow, but he refused.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am never hungry,” he said, “and it is a lucky thing I am not, for my mouth is only painted, and if I should cut a hole in it so I could eat, the straw I am stuffed with would come out, and that would spoil the shape of my head.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy saw at once that this was true, so she only nodded and went on eating her bread.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Tell me something about yourself and the country you came from,” said the Scarecrow, when she had finished her dinner. So she told him all about Kansas, and how gray everything was there, and how the cyclone had carried her to this queer Land of Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow listened carefully, and said, “I cannot understand why you should wish to leave this beautiful country and go back to the dry, gray place you call Kansas.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is because you have no brains” answered the girl. “No matter how dreary and gray our homes are, we people of flesh and blood would rather live there than in any other country, be it ever so beautiful. There is no place like home.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow sighed.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Of course I cannot understand it,” he said. “If your heads were stuffed with straw, like mine, you would probably all live in the beautiful places, and then Kansas would have no people at all. It is fortunate for Kansas that you have brains.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Won’t you tell me a story, while we are resting?” asked the child.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow looked at her reproachfully, and answered:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My life has been so short that I really know nothing whatever. I was only made day before yesterday. What happened in the world before that time is all unknown to me. Luckily, when the farmer made my head, one of the first things he did was to paint my ears, so that I heard what was going on. There was another Munchkin with him, and the first thing I heard was the farmer saying, ‘How do you like those ears?’</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“‘They aren’t straight,’” answered the other.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“‘Never mind,’” said the farmer. “‘They are ears just the same,’” which was true enough.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“‘Now I’ll make the eyes,’” said the farmer. So he painted my right eye, and as soon as it was finished I found myself looking at him and at everything around me with a great deal of curiosity, for this was my first glimpse of the world.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“‘That’s a rather pretty eye,’” remarked the Munchkin who was watching the farmer. “‘Blue paint is just the color for eyes.’</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“‘I think I’ll make the other a little bigger,’” said the farmer. And when the second eye was done I could see much better than before. Then he made my nose and my mouth. But I did not speak, because at that time I didn’t know what a mouth was for. I had the fun of watching them make my body and my arms and legs; and when they fastened on my head, at last, I felt very proud, for I thought I was just as good a man as anyone.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“‘This fellow will scare the crows fast enough,’ said the farmer. ‘He looks just like a man.’</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“‘Why, he is a man,’ said the other, and I quite agreed with him. The farmer carried me under his arm to the cornfield, and set me up on a tall stick, where you found me. He and his friend soon after walked away and left me alone.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I did not like to be deserted this way. So I tried to walk after them. But my feet would not touch the ground, and I was forced to stay on that pole. It was a lonely life to lead, for I had nothing to think of, having been made such a little while before. Many crows and other birds flew into the cornfield, but as soon as they saw me they flew away again, thinking I was a Munchkin; and this pleased me and made me feel that I was quite an important person. By and by an old crow flew near me, and after looking at me carefully he perched upon my shoulder and said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“‘I wonder if that farmer thought to fool me in this clumsy manner. Any crow of sense could see that you are only stuffed with straw.’ Then he hopped down at my feet and ate all the corn he wanted. The other birds, seeing he was not harmed by me, came to eat the corn too, so in a short time there was a great flock of them about me.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I felt sad at this, for it showed I was not such a good Scarecrow after all; but the old crow comforted me, saying, ‘If you only had brains in your head you would be as good a man as any of them, and a better man than some of them. Brains are the only things worth having in this world, no matter whether one is a crow or a man.’</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“After the crows had gone I thought this over, and decided I would try hard to get some brains. By good luck you came along and pulled me off the stake, and from what you say I am sure the Great Oz will give me brains as soon as we get to the Emerald City.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I hope so,” said Dorothy earnestly, “since you seem anxious to have them.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, yes; I am anxious,” returned the Scarecrow. “It is such an uncomfortable feeling to know one is a fool.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well,” said the girl, “let us go.” And she handed the basket to the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>There were no fences at all by the roadside now, and the land was rough and untilled. Toward evening they came to a great forest, where the trees grew so big and close together that their branches met over the road of yellow brick. It was almost dark under the trees, for the branches shut out the daylight; but the travelers did not stop, and went on into the forest.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If this road goes in, it must come out,” said the Scarecrow, “and as the Emerald City is at the other end of the road, we must go wherever it leads us.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Anyone would know that,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Certainly; that is why I know it,” returned the Scarecrow. “If it required brains to figure it out, I never should have said it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>After an hour or so the light faded away, and they found themselves stumbling along in the darkness. Dorothy could not see at all, but Toto could, for some dogs see very well in the dark; and the Scarecrow declared he could see as well as by day. So she took hold of his arm and managed to get along fairly well.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If you see any house, or any place where we can pass the night,” she said, “you must tell me; for it is very uncomfortable walking in the dark.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Soon after the Scarecrow stopped.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I see a little cottage at the right of us,” he said, “built of logs and branches. Shall we go there?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yes, indeed,” answered the child. “I am all tired out.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Scarecrow led her through the trees until they reached the cottage, and Dorothy entered and found a bed of dried leaves in one corner. She lay down at once, and with Toto beside her soon fell into a sound sleep. The Scarecrow, who was never tired, stood up in another corner and waited patiently until morning came.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000383": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000383",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000384": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000384",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter V<br>\nThe Rescue of the Tin Woodman</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000385": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000385",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000386": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000386",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When Dorothy awoke the sun was shining through the trees and Toto had long been out chasing birds around him and squirrels. She sat up and looked around her. There was the Scarecrow, still standing patiently in his corner, waiting for her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000387": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000387",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000388": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000388",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We must go and search for water,” she said to him.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000389": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000389",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000390": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000390",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why do you want water?” he asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000391": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000391",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000392": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000392",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“To wash my face clean after the dust of the road, and to drink, so the dry bread will not stick in my throat.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000393": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000393",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000394": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000394",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It must be inconvenient to be made of flesh,” said the Scarecrow thoughtfully, “for you must sleep, and eat and drink. However, you have brains, and it is worth a lot of bother to be able to think properly.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000395": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000395",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000396": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000396",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They left the cottage and walked through the trees until they found a little spring of clear water, where Dorothy drank and bathed and ate her breakfast. She saw there was not much bread left in the basket, and the girl was thankful the Scarecrow did not have to eat anything, for there was scarcely enough for herself and Toto for the day.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000397": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000397",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000398": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000398",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When she had finished her meal, and was about to go back to the road of yellow brick, she was startled to hear a deep groan near by.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000399": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000399",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000400": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000400",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What was that?” she asked timidly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000401": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000401",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000402": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000402",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I cannot imagine,” replied the Scarecrow; “but we can go and see.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000403": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000403",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000404": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000404",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Just then another groan reached their ears, and the sound seemed to come from behind them. They turned and walked through the forest a few steps, when Dorothy discovered something shining in a ray of sunshine that fell between the trees. She ran to the place and then stopped short, with a little cry of surprise.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000405": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000405",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000406": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000406",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>One of the big trees had been partly chopped through, and standing beside it, with an uplifted axe in his hands, was a man made entirely of tin. His head and arms and legs were jointed upon his body, but he stood perfectly motionless, as if he could not stir at all.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000407": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000407",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000408": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000408",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy looked at him in amazement, and so did the Scarecrow, while Toto barked sharply and made a snap at the tin legs, which hurt his teeth.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000409": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000409",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000410": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000410",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Did you groan?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000411": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000411",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000412": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000412",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yes,” answered the tin man, “I did. I’ve been groaning for more than a year, and no one has ever heard me before or come to help me.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000413": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000413",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000414": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000414",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What can I do for you?” she inquired softly, for she was moved by the sad voice in which the man spoke.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000415": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000415",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000416": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000416",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Get an oil-can and oil my joints,” he answered. “They are rusted so badly that I cannot move them at all; if I am well oiled I shall soon be all right again. You will find an oil-can on a shelf in my cottage.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000417": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000417",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000418": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000418",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy at once ran back to the cottage and found the oil-can, and then she returned and asked anxiously, “Where are your joints?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000419": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000419",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000420": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000420",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oil my neck, first,” replied the Tin Woodman. So she oiled it, and as it was quite badly rusted the Scarecrow took hold of the tin head and moved it gently from side to side until it worked freely, and then the man could turn it himself.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000421": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000421",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000422": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000422",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Now oil the joints in my arms,” he said. And Dorothy oiled them and the Scarecrow bent them carefully until they were quite free from rust and as good as new.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000423": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000423",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000424": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000424",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Tin Woodman gave a sigh of satisfaction and lowered his axe, which he leaned against the tree.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000425": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000425",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000426": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000426",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This is a great comfort,” he said. “I have been holding that axe in the air ever since I rusted, and I’m glad to be able to put it down at last. Now, if you will oil the joints of my legs, I shall be all right once more.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000427": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000427",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000428": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000428",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So they oiled his legs until he could move them freely; and he thanked them again and again for his release, for he seemed a very polite creature, and very grateful.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000429": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000429",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000430": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000430",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I might have stood there always if you had not come along,” he said; “so you have certainly saved my life. How did you happen to be here?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000431": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000431",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000432": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000432",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We are on our way to the Emerald City to see the Great Oz,” she answered, “and we stopped at your cottage to pass the night.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000433": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000433",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000434": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000434",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why do you wish to see Oz?” he asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000435": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000435",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000436": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000436",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I want him to send me back to Kansas, and the Scarecrow wants him to put a few brains into his head,” she replied.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000437": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000437",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000438": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000438",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Tin Woodman appeared to think deeply for a moment. Then he said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000439": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000439",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000440": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000440",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Do you suppose Oz could give me a heart?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000441": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000441",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000442": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000442",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why, I guess so,” Dorothy answered. “It would be as easy as to give the Scarecrow brains.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000443": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000443",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000444": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000444",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“True,” the Tin Woodman returned. “So, if you will allow me to join your party, I will also go to the Emerald City and ask Oz to help me.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000445": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000445",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000446": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000446",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come along,” said the Scarecrow heartily, and Dorothy added that she would be pleased to have his company. So the Tin Woodman shouldered his axe and they all passed through the forest until they came to the road that was paved with yellow brick.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000447": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000447",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000448": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000448",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Tin Woodman had asked Dorothy to put the oil-can in her basket. “For,” he said, “if I should get caught in the rain, and rust again, I would need the oil-can badly.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000449": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000449",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000450": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000450",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>It was a bit of good luck to have their new comrade join the party, for soon after they had begun their journey again they came to a place where the trees and branches grew so thick over the road that the travelers could not pass. But the Tin Woodman set to work with his axe and chopped so well that soon he cleared a passage for the entire party.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000451": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000451",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000452": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000452",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy was thinking so earnestly as they walked along that she did not notice when the Scarecrow stumbled into a hole and rolled over to the side of the road. Indeed he was obliged to call to her to help him up again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000453": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000453",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000454": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000454",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why didn’t you walk around the hole?” asked the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000455": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000455",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000456": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000456",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I don’t know enough,” replied the Scarecrow cheerfully. “My head is stuffed with straw, you know, and that is why I am going to Oz to ask him for some brains.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000457": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000457",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000458": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000458",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, I see,” said the Tin Woodman. “But, after all, brains are not the best things in the world.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000459": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000459",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000460": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000460",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Have you any?” inquired the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000461": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000461",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000462": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000462",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No, my head is quite empty,” answered the Woodman. “But once I had brains, and a heart also; so, having tried them both, I should much rather have a heart.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000463": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000463",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000464": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000464",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And why is that?” asked the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000465": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000465",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000466": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000466",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I will tell you my story, and then you will know.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000467": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000467",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000468": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000468",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So, while they were walking through the forest, the Tin Woodman told the following story:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000469": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000469",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000470": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000470",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I was born the son of a woodman who chopped down trees in the forest and sold the wood for a living. When I grew up, I too became a woodchopper, and after my father died I took care of my old mother as long as she lived. Then I made up my mind that instead of living alone I would marry, so that I might not become lonely.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000471": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000471",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000472": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000472",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“There was one of the Munchkin girls who was so beautiful that I soon grew to love her with all my heart. She, on her part, promised to marry me as soon as I could earn enough money to build a better house for her; so I set to work harder than ever. But the girl lived with an old woman who did not want her to marry anyone, for she was so lazy she wished the girl to remain with her and do the cooking and the housework. So the old woman went to the Wicked Witch of the East, and promised her two sheep and a cow if she would prevent the marriage. Thereupon the Wicked Witch enchanted my axe, and when I was chopping away at my best one day, for I was anxious to get the new house and my wife as soon as possible, the axe slipped all at once and cut off my left leg.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000473": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000473",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000474": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000474",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This at first seemed a great misfortune, for I knew a one-legged man could not do very well as a wood-chopper. So I went to a tinsmith and had him make me a new leg out of tin. The leg worked very well, once I was used to it. But my action angered the Wicked Witch of the East, for she had promised the old woman I should not marry the pretty Munchkin girl. When I began chopping again, my axe slipped and cut off my right leg. Again I went to the tinsmith, and again he made me a leg out of tin. After this the enchanted axe cut off my arms, one after the other; but, nothing daunted, I had them replaced with tin ones. The Wicked Witch then made the axe slip and cut off my head, and at first I thought that was the end of me. But the tinsmith happened to come along, and he made me a new head out of tin.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000475": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000475",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000476": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000476",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I thought I had beaten the Wicked Witch then, and I worked harder than ever; but I little knew how cruel my enemy could be. She thought of a new way to kill my love for the beautiful Munchkin maiden, and made my axe slip again, so that it cut right through my body, splitting me into two halves. Once more the tinsmith came to my help and made me a body of tin, fastening my tin arms and legs and head to it, by means of joints, so that I could move around as well as ever. But, alas! I had now no heart, so that I lost all my love for the Munchkin girl, and did not care whether I married her or not. I suppose she is still living with the old woman, waiting for me to come after her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000477": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000477",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000478": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000478",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My body shone so brightly in the sun that I felt very proud of it and it did not matter now if my axe slipped, for it could not cut me. There was only one danger—that my joints would rust; but I kept an oil-can in my cottage and took care to oil myself whenever I needed it. However, there came a day when I forgot to do this, and, being caught in a rainstorm, before I thought of the danger my joints had rusted, and I was left to stand in the woods until you came to help me. It was a terrible thing to undergo, but during the year I stood there I had time to think that the greatest loss I had known was the loss of my heart. While I was in love I was the happiest man on earth; but no one can love who has not a heart, and so I am resolved to ask Oz to give me one. If he does, I will go back to the Munchkin maiden and marry her.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000479": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000479",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000480": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000480",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Both Dorothy and the Scarecrow had been greatly interested in the story of the Tin Woodman, and now they knew why he was so anxious to get a new heart.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000481": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000481",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000482": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000482",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“All the same,” said the Scarecrow, “I shall ask for brains instead of a heart; for a fool would not know what to do with a heart if he had one.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000483": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000483",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000484": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000484",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I shall take the heart,” returned the Tin Woodman; “for brains do not make one happy, and happiness is the best thing in the world.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000485": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000485",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000486": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000486",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy did not say anything, for she was puzzled to know which of her two friends was right, and she decided if she could only get back to Kansas and Aunt Em, it did not matter so much whether the Woodman had no brains and the Scarecrow no heart, or each got what he wanted.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000487": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000487",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000488": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000488",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>What worried her most was that the bread was nearly gone, and another meal for herself and Toto would empty the basket. To be sure, neither the Woodman nor the Scarecrow ever ate anything, but she was not made of tin nor straw, and could not live unless she was fed.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000489": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000489",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000490": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000490",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000491": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000491",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter VI<br>\nThe Cowardly Lion</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000492": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000492",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000493": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000493",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>All this time Dorothy and her companions had been walking through the thick woods. The road was still paved with yellow brick, but these were much covered by dried branches and dead leaves from the trees, and the walking was not at all good.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000494": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000494",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000495": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000495",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>There were few birds in this part of the forest, for birds love the open country where there is plenty of sunshine. But now and then there came a deep growl from some wild animal hidden among the trees. These sounds made the little girl’s heart beat fast, for she did not know what made them; but Toto knew, and he walked close to Dorothy’s side, and did not even bark in return.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000496": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000496",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000497": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000497",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How long will it be,” the child asked of the Tin Woodman, “before we are out of the forest?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000498": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000498",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000499": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000499",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I cannot tell,” was the answer, “for I have never been to the Emerald City. But my father went there once, when I was a boy, and he said it was a long journey through a dangerous country, although nearer to the city where Oz dwells the country is beautiful. But I am not afraid so long as I have my oil-can, and nothing can hurt the Scarecrow, while you bear upon your forehead the mark of the Good Witch’s kiss, and that will protect you from harm.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000500": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000500",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000501": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000501",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But Toto!” said the girl anxiously. “What will protect him?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000502": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000502",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000503": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000503",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We must protect him ourselves if he is in danger,” replied the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000504": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000504",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000505": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000505",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Just as he spoke there came from the forest a terrible roar, and the next moment a great Lion bounded into the road. With one blow of his paw he sent the Scarecrow spinning over and over to the edge of the road, and then he struck at the Tin Woodman with his sharp claws. But, to the Lion’s surprise, he could make no impression on the tin, although the Woodman fell over in the road and lay still.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000506": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000506",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000507": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000507",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Little Toto, now that he had an enemy to face, ran barking toward the Lion, and the great beast had opened his mouth to bite the dog, when Dorothy, fearing Toto would be killed, and heedless of danger, rushed forward and slapped the Lion upon his nose as hard as she could, while she cried out:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000508": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000508",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000509": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000509",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Don’t you dare to bite Toto! You ought to be ashamed of yourself, a big beast like you, to bite a poor little dog!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000510": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000510",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000511": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000511",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I didn’t bite him,” said the Lion, as he rubbed his nose with his paw where Dorothy had hit it.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000512": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000512",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000513": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000513",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No, but you tried to,” she retorted. “You are nothing but a big coward.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000514": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000514",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000515": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000515",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I know it,” said the Lion, hanging his head in shame. “I’ve always known it. But how can I help it?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000516": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000516",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000517": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000517",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I don’t know, I’m sure. To think of your striking a stuffed man, like the poor Scarecrow!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000518": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000518",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000519": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000519",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Is he stuffed?” asked the Lion in surprise, as he watched her pick up the Scarecrow and set him upon his feet, while she patted him into shape again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000520": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000520",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000521": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000521",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Of course he’s stuffed,” replied Dorothy, who was still angry.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000522": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000522",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000523": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000523",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That’s why he went over so easily,” remarked the Lion. “It astonished me to see him whirl around so. Is the other one stuffed also?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000524": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000524",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000525": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000525",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No,” said Dorothy, “he’s made of tin.” And she helped the Woodman up again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000526": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000526",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000527": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000527",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That’s why he nearly blunted my claws,” said the Lion. “When they scratched against the tin it made a cold shiver run down my back. What is that little animal you are so tender of?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000528": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000528",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000529": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000529",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“He is my dog, Toto,” answered Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000530": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000530",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000531": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000531",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Is he made of tin, or stuffed?” asked the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000532": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000532",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000533": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000533",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Neither. He’s a—a—a meat dog,” said the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000534": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000534",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000535": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000535",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh! He’s a curious animal and seems remarkably small, now that I look at him. No one would think of biting such a little thing, except a coward like me,” continued the Lion sadly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000536": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000536",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000537": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000537",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What makes you a coward?” asked Dorothy, looking at the great beast in wonder, for he was as big as a small horse.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000538": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000538",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000539": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000539",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It’s a mystery,” replied the Lion. “I suppose I was born that way. All the other animals in the forest naturally expect me to be brave, for the Lion is everywhere thought to be the King of Beasts. I learned that if I roared very loudly every living thing was frightened and got out of my way. Whenever I’ve met a man I’ve been awfully scared; but I just roared at him, and he has always run away as fast as he could go. If the elephants and the tigers and the bears had ever tried to fight me, I should have run myself—I’m such a coward; but just as soon as they hear me roar they all try to get away from me, and of course I let them go.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000540": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000540",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000541": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000541",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But that isn’t right. The King of Beasts shouldn’t be a coward,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000542": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000542",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000543": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000543",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I know it,” returned the Lion, wiping a tear from his eye with the tip of his tail. “It is my great sorrow, and makes my life very unhappy. But whenever there is danger, my heart begins to beat fast.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000544": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000544",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000545": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000545",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Perhaps you have heart disease,” said the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000546": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000546",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000547": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000547",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It may be,” said the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000549": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000549",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If you have,” continued the Tin Woodman, “you ought to be glad, for it proves you have a heart. For my part, I have no heart; so I cannot have heart disease.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000550": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000550",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000551": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000551",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Perhaps,” said the Lion thoughtfully, “if I had no heart I should not be a coward.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000552": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000552",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000553": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000553",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Have you brains?” asked the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000554": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000554",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000555": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000555",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I suppose so. I’ve never looked to see,” replied the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000556": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000556",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000557": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000557",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am going to the Great Oz to ask him to give me some,” remarked the Scarecrow, “for my head is stuffed with straw.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000558": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000558",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000559": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000559",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I am going to ask him to give me a heart,” said the Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000560": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000560",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000561": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000561",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I am going to ask him to send Toto and me back to Kansas,” added Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000562": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000562",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000563": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000563",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Do you think Oz could give me courage?” asked the Cowardly Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000564": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000564",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000565": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000565",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Just as easily as he could give me brains,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000566": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000566",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000567": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000567",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Or give me a heart,” said the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000568": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000568",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000569": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000569",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Or send me back to Kansas,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000570": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000570",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000571": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000571",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Then, if you don’t mind, I’ll go with you,” said the Lion, “for my life is simply unbearable without a bit of courage.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000572": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000572",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000573": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000573",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You will be very welcome,” answered Dorothy, “for you will help to keep away the other wild beasts. It seems to me they must be more cowardly than you are if they allow you to scare them so easily.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000574": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000574",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000575": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000575",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“They really are,” said the Lion, “but that doesn’t make me any braver, and as long as I know myself to be a coward I shall be unhappy.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000576": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000576",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000577": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000577",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So once more the little company set off upon the journey, the Lion walking with stately strides at Dorothy’s side. Toto did not approve of this new comrade at first, for he could not forget how nearly he had been crushed between the Lion’s great jaws. But after a time he became more at ease, and presently Toto and the Cowardly Lion had grown to be good friends.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000578": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000578",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000579": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000579",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>During the rest of that day there was no other adventure to mar the peace of their journey. Once, indeed, the Tin Woodman stepped upon a beetle that was crawling along the road, and killed the poor little thing. This made the Tin Woodman very unhappy, for he was always careful not to hurt any living creature; and as he walked along he wept several tears of sorrow and regret. These tears ran slowly down his face and over the hinges of his jaw, and there they rusted. When Dorothy presently asked him a question the Tin Woodman could not open his mouth, for his jaws were tightly rusted together. He became greatly frightened at this and made many motions to Dorothy to relieve him, but she could not understand. The Lion was also puzzled to know what was wrong. But the Scarecrow seized the oil-can from Dorothy’s basket and oiled the Woodman’s jaws, so that after a few moments he could talk as well as before.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000580": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000580",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000581": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000581",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This will serve me a lesson,” said he, “to look where I step. For if I should kill another bug or beetle I should surely cry again, and crying rusts my jaws so that I cannot speak.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000582": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000582",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000583": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000583",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Thereafter he walked very carefully, with his eyes on the road, and when he saw a tiny ant toiling by he would step over it, so as not to harm it. The Tin Woodman knew very well he had no heart, and therefore he took great care never to be cruel or unkind to anything.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000584": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000584",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000585": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000585",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You people with hearts,” he said, “have something to guide you, and need never do wrong; but I have no heart, and so I must be very careful. When Oz gives me a heart of course I needn’t mind so much.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000586": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000586",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000587": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000587",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000588": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000588",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter VII<br>\nThe Journey to the Great Oz</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000589": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000589",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000590": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000590",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They were obliged to camp out that night under a large tree in the forest, for there were no houses near. The tree made a good, thick covering to protect them from the dew, and the Tin Woodman chopped a great pile of wood with his axe and Dorothy built a splendid fire that warmed her and made her feel less lonely. She and Toto ate the last of their bread, and now she did not know what they would do for breakfast.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000591": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000591",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000592": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000592",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If you wish,” said the Lion, “I will go into the forest and kill a deer for you. You can roast it by the fire, since your tastes are so peculiar that you prefer cooked food, and then you will have a very good breakfast.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000593": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000593",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000594": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000594",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Don’t! Please don’t,” begged the Tin Woodman. “I should certainly weep if you killed a poor deer, and then my jaws would rust again.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000595": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000595",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000596": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000596",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the Lion went away into the forest and found his own supper, and no one ever knew what it was, for he didn’t mention it. And the Scarecrow found a tree full of nuts and filled Dorothy’s basket with them, so that she would not be hungry for a long time. She thought this was very kind and thoughtful of the Scarecrow, but she laughed heartily at the awkward way in which the poor creature picked up the nuts. His padded hands were so clumsy and the nuts were so small that he dropped almost as many as he put in the basket. But the Scarecrow did not mind how long it took him to fill the basket, for it enabled him to keep away from the fire, as he feared a spark might get into his straw and burn him up. So he kept a good distance away from the flames, and only came near to cover Dorothy with dry leaves when she lay down to sleep. These kept her very snug and warm, and she slept soundly until morning.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000597": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000597",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000598": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000598",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When it was daylight, the girl bathed her face in a little rippling brook, and soon after they all started toward the Emerald City.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000599": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000599",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000600": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000600",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>This was to be an eventful day for the travelers. They had hardly been walking an hour when they saw before them a great ditch that crossed the road and divided the forest as far as they could see on either side. It was a very wide ditch, and when they crept up to the edge and looked into it they could see it was also very deep, and there were many big, jagged rocks at the bottom. The sides were so steep that none of them could climb down, and for a moment it seemed that their journey must end.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000601": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000601",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000602": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000602",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What shall we do?” asked Dorothy despairingly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000603": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000603",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000604": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000604",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I haven’t the faintest idea,” said the Tin Woodman, and the Lion shook his shaggy mane and looked thoughtful.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000605": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000605",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000606": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000606",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the Scarecrow said, “We cannot fly, that is certain. Neither can we climb down into this great ditch. Therefore, if we cannot jump over it, we must stop where we are.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000607": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000607",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000608": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000608",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I think I could jump over it,” said the Cowardly Lion, after measuring the distance carefully in his mind.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000609": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000609",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000610": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000610",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Then we are all right,” answered the Scarecrow, “for you can carry us all over on your back, one at a time.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000611": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000611",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000612": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000612",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well, I’ll try it,” said the Lion. “Who will go first?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000613": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000613",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000614": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000614",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I will,” declared the Scarecrow, “for, if you found that you could not jump over the gulf, Dorothy would be killed, or the Tin Woodman badly dented on the rocks below. But if I am on your back it will not matter so much, for the fall would not hurt me at all.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000615": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000615",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000616": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000616",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am terribly afraid of falling, myself,” said the Cowardly Lion, “but I suppose there is nothing to do but try it. So get on my back and we will make the attempt.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000617": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000617",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000618": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000618",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow sat upon the Lion’s back, and the big beast walked to the edge of the gulf and crouched down.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000619": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000619",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000620": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000620",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why don’t you run and jump?” asked the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000621": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000621",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000622": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000622",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Because that isn’t the way we Lions do these things,” he replied. Then giving a great spring, he shot through the air and landed safely on the other side. They were all greatly pleased to see how easily he did it, and after the Scarecrow had got down from his back the Lion sprang across the ditch again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000623": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000623",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000624": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000624",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy thought she would go next; so she took Toto in her arms and climbed on the Lion’s back, holding tightly to his mane with one hand. The next moment it seemed as if she were flying through the air; and then, before she had time to think about it, she was safe on the other side. The Lion went back a third time and got the Tin Woodman, and then they all sat down for a few moments to give the beast a chance to rest, for his great leaps had made his breath short, and he panted like a big dog that has been running too long.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000625": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000625",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000626": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000626",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They found the forest very thick on this side, and it looked dark and gloomy. After the Lion had rested they started along the road of yellow brick, silently wondering, each in his own mind, if ever they would come to the end of the woods and reach the bright sunshine again. To add to their discomfort, they soon heard strange noises in the depths of the forest, and the Lion whispered to them that it was in this part of the country that the Kalidahs lived.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000627": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000627",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000628": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000628",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What are the Kalidahs?” asked the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000629": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000629",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000630": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000630",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“They are monstrous beasts with bodies like bears and heads like tigers,” replied the Lion, “and with claws so long and sharp that they could tear me in two as easily as I could kill Toto. I’m terribly afraid of the Kalidahs.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000631": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000631",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000632": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000632",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I’m not surprised that you are,” returned Dorothy. “They must be dreadful beasts.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000633": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000633",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000634": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000634",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion was about to reply when suddenly they came to another gulf across the road. But this one was so broad and deep that the Lion knew at once he could not leap across it.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000635": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000635",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000636": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000636",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So they sat down to consider what they should do, and after serious thought the Scarecrow said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000637": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000637",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000638": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000638",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Here is a great tree, standing close to the ditch. If the Tin Woodman can chop it down, so that it will fall to the other side, we can walk across it easily.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000639": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000639",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000640": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000640",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is a first-rate idea,” said the Lion. “One would almost suspect you had brains in your head, instead of straw.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000641": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000641",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000642": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000642",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Woodman set to work at once, and so sharp was his axe that the tree was soon chopped nearly through. Then the Lion put his strong front legs against the tree and pushed with all his might, and slowly the big tree tipped and fell with a crash across the ditch, with its top branches on the other side.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000643": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000643",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000644": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000644",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They had just started to cross this queer bridge when a sharp growl made them all look up, and to their horror they saw running toward them two great beasts with bodies like bears and heads like tigers.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000645": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000645",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000646": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000646",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“They are the Kalidahs!” said the Cowardly Lion, beginning to tremble.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000647": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000647",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000648": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000648",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Quick!” cried the Scarecrow. “Let us cross over.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000649": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000649",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000650": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000650",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So Dorothy went first, holding Toto in her arms, the Tin Woodman followed, and the Scarecrow came next. The Lion, although he was certainly afraid, turned to face the Kalidahs, and then he gave so loud and terrible a roar that Dorothy screamed and the Scarecrow fell over backward, while even the fierce beasts stopped short and looked at him in surprise.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000651": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000651",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000652": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000652",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But, seeing they were bigger than the Lion, and remembering that there were two of them and only one of him, the Kalidahs again rushed forward, and the Lion crossed over the tree and turned to see what they would do next. Without stopping an instant the fierce beasts also began to cross the tree. And the Lion said to Dorothy:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000653": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000653",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000654": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000654",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We are lost, for they will surely tear us to pieces with their sharp claws. But stand close behind me, and I will fight them as long as I am alive.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000655": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000655",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000656": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000656",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Wait a minute!” called the Scarecrow. He had been thinking what was best to be done, and now he asked the Woodman to chop away the end of the tree that rested on their side of the ditch. The Tin Woodman began to use his axe at once, and, just as the two Kalidahs were nearly across, the tree fell with a crash into the gulf, carrying the ugly, snarling brutes with it, and both were dashed to pieces on the sharp rocks at the bottom.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000657": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000657",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000658": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000658",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well,” said the Cowardly Lion, drawing a long breath of relief, “I see we are going to live a little while longer, and I am glad of it, for it must be a very uncomfortable thing not to be alive. Those creatures frightened me so badly that my heart is beating yet.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000659": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000659",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000660": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000660",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Ah,” said the Tin Woodman sadly, “I wish I had a heart to beat.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000661": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000661",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000662": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000662",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>This adventure made the travelers more anxious than ever to get out of the forest, and they walked so fast that Dorothy became tired, and had to ride on the Lion’s back. To their great joy the trees became thinner the farther they advanced, and in the afternoon they suddenly came upon a broad river, flowing swiftly just before them. On the other side of the water they could see the road of yellow brick running through a beautiful country, with green meadows dotted with bright flowers and all the road bordered with trees hanging full of delicious fruits. They were greatly pleased to see this delightful country before them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000663": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000663",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000664": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000664",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How shall we cross the river?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000665": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000665",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000666": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000666",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is easily done,” replied the Scarecrow. “The Tin Woodman must build us a raft, so we can float to the other side.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000667": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000667",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000668": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000668",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Woodman took his axe and began to chop down small trees to make a raft, and while he was busy at this the Scarecrow found on the riverbank a tree full of fine fruit. This pleased Dorothy, who had eaten nothing but nuts all day, and she made a hearty meal of the ripe fruit.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000669": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000669",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000670": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000670",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But it takes time to make a raft, even when one is as industrious and untiring as the Tin Woodman, and when night came the work was not done. So they found a cozy place under the trees where they slept well until the morning; and Dorothy dreamed of the Emerald City, and of the good Wizard Oz, who would soon send her back to her own home again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000671": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000671",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000672": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000672",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000673": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000673",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter VIII<br>\nThe Deadly Poppy Field</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000674": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000674",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000675": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000675",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Our little party of travelers awakened the next morning refreshed and full of hope, and Dorothy breakfasted like a princess off peaches and plums from the trees beside the river. Behind them was the dark forest they had passed safely through, although they had suffered many discouragements; but before them was a lovely, sunny country that seemed to beckon them on to the Emerald City.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000676": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000676",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000677": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000677",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>To be sure, the broad river now cut them off from this beautiful land. But the raft was nearly done, and after the Tin Woodman had cut a few more logs and fastened them together with wooden pins, they were ready to start. Dorothy sat down in the middle of the raft and held Toto in her arms. When the Cowardly Lion stepped upon the raft it tipped badly, for he was big and heavy; but the Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman stood upon the other end to steady it, and they had long poles in their hands to push the raft through the water.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000678": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000678",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000679": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000679",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They got along quite well at first, but when they reached the middle of the river the swift current swept the raft downstream, farther and farther away from the road of yellow brick. And the water grew so deep that the long poles would not touch the bottom.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000680": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000680",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000681": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000681",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This is bad,” said the Tin Woodman, “for if we cannot get to the land we shall be carried into the country of the Wicked Witch of the West, and she will enchant us and make us her slaves.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000682": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000682",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000683": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000683",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And then I should get no brains,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000684": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000684",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000685": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000685",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I should get no courage,” said the Cowardly Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000686": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000686",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000687": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000687",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I should get no heart,” said the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000688": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000688",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000689": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000689",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I should never get back to Kansas,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000690": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000690",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000691": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000691",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We must certainly get to the Emerald City if we can,” the Scarecrow continued, and he pushed so hard on his long pole that it stuck fast in the mud at the bottom of the river. Then, before he could pull it out again—or let go—the raft was swept away, and the poor Scarecrow was left clinging to the pole in the middle of the river.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000692": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000692",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000693": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000693",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Good-bye!” he called after them, and they were very sorry to leave him. Indeed, the Tin Woodman began to cry, but fortunately remembered that he might rust, and so dried his tears on Dorothy’s apron.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000694": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000694",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000695": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000695",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Of course this was a bad thing for the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000696": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000696",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000697": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000697",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am now worse off than when I first met Dorothy,” he thought. “Then, I was stuck on a pole in a cornfield, where I could make-believe scare the crows, at any rate. But surely there is no use for a Scarecrow stuck on a pole in the middle of a river. I am afraid I shall never have any brains, after all!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000698": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000698",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000699": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000699",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Down the stream the raft floated, and the poor Scarecrow was left far behind. Then the Lion said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000700": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000700",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000701": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000701",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Something must be done to save us. I think I can swim to the shore and pull the raft after me, if you will only hold fast to the tip of my tail.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000702": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000702",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000703": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000703",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So he sprang into the water, and the Tin Woodman caught fast hold of his tail. Then the Lion began to swim with all his might toward the shore. It was hard work, although he was so big; but by and by they were drawn out of the current, and then Dorothy took the Tin Woodman’s long pole and helped push the raft to the land.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000704": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000704",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000705": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000705",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They were all tired out when they reached the shore at last and stepped off upon the pretty green grass, and they also knew that the stream had carried them a long way past the road of yellow brick that led to the Emerald City.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000706": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000706",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000707": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000707",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What shall we do now?” asked the Tin Woodman, as the Lion lay down on the grass to let the sun dry him.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000708": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000708",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000709": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000709",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We must get back to the road, in some way,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000710": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000710",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000711": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000711",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The best plan will be to walk along the riverbank until we come to the road again,” remarked the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000712": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000712",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000713": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000713",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So, when they were rested, Dorothy picked up her basket and they started along the grassy bank, to the road from which the river had carried them. It was a lovely country, with plenty of flowers and fruit trees and sunshine to cheer them, and had they not felt so sorry for the poor Scarecrow, they could have been very happy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000714": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000714",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000715": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000715",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They walked along as fast as they could, Dorothy only stopping once to pick a beautiful flower; and after a time the Tin Woodman cried out: “Look!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000716": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000716",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000717": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000717",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then they all looked at the river and saw the Scarecrow perched upon his pole in the middle of the water, looking very lonely and sad.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000718": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000718",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000719": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000719",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What can we do to save him?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000720": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000720",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000721": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000721",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion and the Woodman both shook their heads, for they did not know. So they sat down upon the bank and gazed wistfully at the Scarecrow until a Stork flew by, who, upon seeing them, stopped to rest at the water’s edge.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000722": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000722",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000723": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000723",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Who are you and where are you going?” asked the Stork.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000724": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000724",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000725": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000725",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am Dorothy,” answered the girl, “and these are my friends, the Tin Woodman and the Cowardly Lion; and we are going to the Emerald City.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000726": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000726",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000727": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000727",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This isn’t the road,” said the Stork, as she twisted her long neck and looked sharply at the queer party.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000728": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000728",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000729": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000729",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I know it,” returned Dorothy, “but we have lost the Scarecrow, and are wondering how we shall get him again.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000730": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000730",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000731": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000731",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Where is he?” asked the Stork.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000732": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000732",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000733": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000733",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Over there in the river,” answered the little girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000734": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000734",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000735": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000735",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If he wasn’t so big and heavy I would get him for you,” remarked the Stork.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000736": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000736",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000737": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000737",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“He isn’t heavy a bit,” said Dorothy eagerly, “for he is stuffed with straw; and if you will bring him back to us, we shall thank you ever and ever so much.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000738": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000738",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000739": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000739",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well, I’ll try,” said the Stork, “but if I find he is too heavy to carry I shall have to drop him in the river again.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000740": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000740",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000741": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000741",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the big bird flew into the air and over the water till she came to where the Scarecrow was perched upon his pole. Then the Stork with her great claws grabbed the Scarecrow by the arm and carried him up into the air and back to the bank, where Dorothy and the Lion and the Tin Woodman and Toto were sitting.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000742": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000742",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000743": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000743",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When the Scarecrow found himself among his friends again, he was so happy that he hugged them all, even the Lion and Toto; and as they walked along he sang “Tol-de-ri-de-oh!” at every step, he felt so gay.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000744": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000744",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000745": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000745",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I was afraid I should have to stay in the river forever,” he said, “but the kind Stork saved me, and if I ever get any brains I shall find the Stork again and do her some kindness in return.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000746": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000746",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000747": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000747",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That’s all right,” said the Stork, who was flying along beside them. “I always like to help anyone in trouble. But I must go now, for my babies are waiting in the nest for me. I hope you will find the Emerald City and that Oz will help you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000748": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000748",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000749": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000749",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Thank you,” replied Dorothy, and then the kind Stork flew into the air and was soon out of sight.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000750": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000750",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000751": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000751",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They walked along listening to the singing of the brightly colored birds and looking at the lovely flowers which now became so thick that the ground was carpeted with them. There were big yellow and white and blue and purple blossoms, besides great clusters of scarlet poppies, which were so brilliant in color they almost dazzled Dorothy’s eyes.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000752": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000752",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000753": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000753",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Aren’t they beautiful?” the girl asked, as she breathed in the spicy scent of the bright flowers.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000754": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000754",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000755": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000755",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I suppose so,” answered the Scarecrow. “When I have brains, I shall probably like them better.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000756": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000756",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000757": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000757",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If I only had a heart, I should love them,” added the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000758": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000758",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000759": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000759",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I always did like flowers,” said the Lion. “They seem so helpless and frail. But there are none in the forest so bright as these.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They now came upon more and more of the big scarlet poppies, and fewer and fewer of the other flowers; and soon they found themselves in the midst of a great meadow of poppies. Now it is well known that when there are many of these flowers together their odor is so powerful that anyone who breathes it falls asleep, and if the sleeper is not carried away from the scent of the flowers, he sleeps on and on forever. But Dorothy did not know this, nor could she get away from the bright red flowers that were everywhere about; so presently her eyes grew heavy and she felt she must sit down to rest and to sleep.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the Tin Woodman would not let her do this.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We must hurry and get back to the road of yellow brick before dark,” he said; and the Scarecrow agreed with him. So they kept walking until Dorothy could stand no longer. Her eyes closed in spite of herself and she forgot where she was and fell among the poppies, fast asleep.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000766": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000766",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000767": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000767",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What shall we do?” asked the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000768": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000768",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000769": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000769",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If we leave her here she will die,” said the Lion. “The smell of the flowers is killing us all. I myself can scarcely keep my eyes open, and the dog is asleep already.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000770": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000770",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000771": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000771",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>It was true; Toto had fallen down beside his little mistress. But the Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman, not being made of flesh, were not troubled by the scent of the flowers.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000772": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000772",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000773": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000773",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Run fast,” said the Scarecrow to the Lion, “and get out of this deadly flower bed as soon as you can. We will bring the little girl with us, but if you should fall asleep you are too big to be carried.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000774": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000774",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000775": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000775",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Lion aroused himself and bounded forward as fast as he could go. In a moment he was out of sight.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000776": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000776",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000777": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000777",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Let us make a chair with our hands and carry her,” said the Scarecrow. So they picked up Toto and put the dog in Dorothy’s lap, and then they made a chair with their hands for the seat and their arms for the arms and carried the sleeping girl between them through the flowers.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000778": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000778",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000779": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000779",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>On and on they walked, and it seemed that the great carpet of deadly flowers that surrounded them would never end. They followed the bend of the river, and at last came upon their friend the Lion, lying fast asleep among the poppies. The flowers had been too strong for the huge beast and he had given up at last, and fallen only a short distance from the end of the poppy bed, where the sweet grass spread in beautiful green fields before them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000780": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000780",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000781": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000781",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We can do nothing for him,” said the Tin Woodman, sadly; “for he is much too heavy to lift. We must leave him here to sleep on forever, and perhaps he will dream that he has found courage at last.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000782": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000782",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000783": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000783",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I’m sorry,” said the Scarecrow. “The Lion was a very good comrade for one so cowardly. But let us go on.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000784": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000784",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000785": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000785",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They carried the sleeping girl to a pretty spot beside the river, far enough from the poppy field to prevent her breathing any more of the poison of the flowers, and here they laid her gently on the soft grass and waited for the fresh breeze to waken her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000786": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000786",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000787": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000787",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000788": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000788",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter IX<br>\nThe Queen of the Field Mice</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000789": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000789",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000790": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000790",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We cannot be far from the road of yellow brick, now,” remarked the Scarecrow, as he stood beside the girl, “for we have come nearly as far as the river carried us away.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000791": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000791",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000792": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000792",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Tin Woodman was about to reply when he heard a low growl, and turning his head (which worked beautifully on hinges) he saw a strange beast come bounding over the grass toward them. It was, indeed, a great yellow Wildcat, and the Woodman thought it must be chasing something, for its ears were lying close to its head and its mouth was wide open, showing two rows of ugly teeth, while its red eyes glowed like balls of fire. As it came nearer the Tin Woodman saw that running before the beast was a little gray field mouse, and although he had no heart he knew it was wrong for the Wildcat to try to kill such a pretty, harmless creature.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000793": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000793",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000794": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000794",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Woodman raised his axe, and as the Wildcat ran by he gave it a quick blow that cut the beast’s head clean off from its body, and it rolled over at his feet in two pieces.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000795": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000795",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000796": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000796",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The field mouse, now that it was freed from its enemy, stopped short; and coming slowly up to the Woodman it said, in a squeaky little voice:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000797": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000797",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000798": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000798",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, thank you! Thank you ever so much for saving my life.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000799": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000799",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000800": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000800",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Don’t speak of it, I beg of you,” replied the Woodman. “I have no heart, you know, so I am careful to help all those who may need a friend, even if it happens to be only a mouse.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000801": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000801",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000802": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000802",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Only a mouse!” cried the little animal, indignantly. “Why, I am a Queen—the Queen of all the Field Mice!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000803": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000803",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000804": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000804",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, indeed,” said the Woodman, making a bow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000805": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000805",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000806": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000806",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Therefore you have done a great deed, as well as a brave one, in saving my life,” added the Queen.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000807": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000807",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000808": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000808",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>At that moment several mice were seen running up as fast as their little legs could carry them, and when they saw their Queen they exclaimed:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000809": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000809",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000810": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000810",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, your Majesty, we thought you would be killed! How did you manage to escape the great Wildcat?” They all bowed so low to the little Queen that they almost stood upon their heads.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000811": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000811",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000812": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000812",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This funny tin man,” she answered, “killed the Wildcat and saved my life. So hereafter you must all serve him, and obey his slightest wish.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000813": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000813",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000814": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000814",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We will!” cried all the mice, in a shrill chorus. And then they scampered in all directions, for Toto had awakened from his sleep, and seeing all these mice around him he gave one bark of delight and jumped right into the middle of the group. Toto had always loved to chase mice when he lived in Kansas, and he saw no harm in it.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000815": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000815",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000816": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000816",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the Tin Woodman caught the dog in his arms and held him tight, while he called to the mice, “Come back! Come back! Toto shall not hurt you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000817": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000817",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000818": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000818",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>At this the Queen of the Mice stuck her head out from underneath a clump of grass and asked, in a timid voice, “Are you sure he will not bite us?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000819": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000819",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000820": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000820",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I will not let him,” said the Woodman; “so do not be afraid.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000821": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000821",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000822": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000822",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>One by one the mice came creeping back, and Toto did not bark again, although he tried to get out of the Woodman’s arms, and would have bitten him had he not known very well he was made of tin. Finally one of the biggest mice spoke.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000823": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000823",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000824": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000824",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Is there anything we can do,” it asked, “to repay you for saving the life of our Queen?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000825": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000825",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000826": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000826",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Nothing that I know of,” answered the Woodman; but the Scarecrow, who had been trying to think, but could not because his head was stuffed with straw, said, quickly, “Oh, yes; you can save our friend, the Cowardly Lion, who is asleep in the poppy bed.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000827": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000827",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000828": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000828",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“A Lion!” cried the little Queen. “Why, he would eat us all up.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000829": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000829",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000830": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000830",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, no,” declared the Scarecrow; “this Lion is a coward.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000831": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000831",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000832": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000832",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Really?” asked the Mouse.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000833": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000833",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000834": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000834",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“He says so himself,” answered the Scarecrow, “and he would never hurt anyone who is our friend. If you will help us to save him I promise that he shall treat you all with kindness.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000835": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000835",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000836": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000836",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Very well,” said the Queen, “we trust you. But what shall we do?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000837": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000837",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000838": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000838",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Are there many of these mice which call you Queen and are willing to obey you?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000839": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000839",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000840": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000840",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, yes; there are thousands,” she replied.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000841": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000841",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000842": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000842",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Then send for them all to come here as soon as possible, and let each one bring a long piece of string.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000843": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000843",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000844": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000844",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Queen turned to the mice that attended her and told them to go at once and get all her people. As soon as they heard her orders they ran away in every direction as fast as possible.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000845": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000845",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000846": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000846",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Now,” said the Scarecrow to the Tin Woodman, “you must go to those trees by the riverside and make a truck that will carry the Lion.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000847": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000847",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000848": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000848",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Woodman went at once to the trees and began to work; and he soon made a truck out of the limbs of trees, from which he chopped away all the leaves and branches. He fastened it together with wooden pegs and made the four wheels out of short pieces of a big tree trunk. So fast and so well did he work that by the time the mice began to arrive the truck was all ready for them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000849": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000849",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000850": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000850",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They came from all directions, and there were thousands of them: big mice and little mice and middle-sized mice; and each one brought a piece of string in his mouth. It was about this time that Dorothy woke from her long sleep and opened her eyes. She was greatly astonished to find herself lying upon the grass, with thousands of mice standing around and looking at her timidly. But the Scarecrow told her about everything, and turning to the dignified little Mouse, he said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000851": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000851",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000852": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000852",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Permit me to introduce to you her Majesty, the Queen.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000853": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000853",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000854": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000854",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy nodded gravely and the Queen made a curtsy, after which she became quite friendly with the little girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000855": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000855",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000856": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000856",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow and the Woodman now began to fasten the mice to the truck, using the strings they had brought. One end of a string was tied around the neck of each mouse and the other end to the truck. Of course the truck was a thousand times bigger than any of the mice who were to draw it; but when all the mice had been harnessed, they were able to pull it quite easily. Even the Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman could sit on it, and were drawn swiftly by their queer little horses to the place where the Lion lay asleep.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000857": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000857",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000858": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000858",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>After a great deal of hard work, for the Lion was heavy, they managed to get him up on the truck. Then the Queen hurriedly gave her people the order to start, for she feared if the mice stayed among the poppies too long they also would fall asleep.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000859": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000859",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000860": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000860",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>At first the little creatures, many though they were, could hardly stir the heavily loaded truck; but the Woodman and the Scarecrow both pushed from behind, and they got along better. Soon they rolled the Lion out of the poppy bed to the green fields, where he could breathe the sweet, fresh air again, instead of the poisonous scent of the flowers.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000861": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000861",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000862": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000862",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy came to meet them and thanked the little mice warmly for saving her companion from death. She had grown so fond of the big Lion she was glad he had been rescued.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000863": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000863",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000864": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000864",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then the mice were unharnessed from the truck and scampered away through the grass to their homes. The Queen of the Mice was the last to leave.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000865": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000865",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000866": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000866",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If ever you need us again,” she said, “come out into the field and call, and we shall hear you and come to your assistance. Good-bye!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000867": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000867",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000868": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000868",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Good-bye!” they all answered, and away the Queen ran, while Dorothy held Toto tightly lest he should run after her and frighten her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000869": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000869",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000870": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000870",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>After this they sat down beside the Lion until he should awaken; and the Scarecrow brought Dorothy some fruit from a tree near by, which she ate for her dinner.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000871": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000871",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000872": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000872",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000873": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000873",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter X<br>\nThe Guardian of the Gate</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000874": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000874",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000875": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000875",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>It was some time before the Cowardly Lion awakened, for he had lain among the poppies a long while, breathing in their deadly fragrance; but when he did open his eyes and roll off the truck he was very glad to find himself still alive.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000876": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000876",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000877": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000877",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I ran as fast as I could,” he said, sitting down and yawning, “but the flowers were too strong for me. How did you get me out?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000878": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000878",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000879": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000879",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then they told him of the field mice, and how they had generously saved him from death; and the Cowardly Lion laughed, and said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000880": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000880",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000881": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000881",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I have always thought myself very big and terrible; yet such little things as flowers came near to killing me, and such small animals as mice have saved my life. How strange it all is! But, comrades, what shall we do now?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000882": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000882",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000883": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000883",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We must journey on until we find the road of yellow brick again,” said Dorothy, “and then we can keep on to the Emerald City.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000884": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000884",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000885": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000885",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So, the Lion being fully refreshed, and feeling quite himself again, they all started upon the journey, greatly enjoying the walk through the soft, fresh grass; and it was not long before they reached the road of yellow brick and turned again toward the Emerald City where the Great Oz dwelt.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000886": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000886",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000887": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000887",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The road was smooth and well paved, now, and the country about was beautiful, so that the travelers rejoiced in leaving the forest far behind, and with it the many dangers they had met in its gloomy shades. Once more they could see fences built beside the road; but these were painted green, and when they came to a small house, in which a farmer evidently lived, that also was painted green. They passed by several of these houses during the afternoon, and sometimes people came to the doors and looked at them as if they would like to ask questions; but no one came near them nor spoke to them because of the great Lion, of which they were very much afraid. The people were all dressed in clothing of a lovely emerald-green color and wore peaked hats like those of the Munchkins.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000888": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000888",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000889": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000889",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This must be the Land of Oz,” said Dorothy, “and we are surely getting near the Emerald City.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000890": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000890",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000891": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000891",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yes,” answered the Scarecrow. “Everything is green here, while in the country of the Munchkins blue was the favorite color. But the people do not seem to be as friendly as the Munchkins, and I’m afraid we shall be unable to find a place to pass the night.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000892": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000892",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000893": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000893",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I should like something to eat besides fruit,” said the girl, “and I’m sure Toto is nearly starved. Let us stop at the next house and talk to the people.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000894": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000894",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000895": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000895",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So, when they came to a good-sized farmhouse, Dorothy walked boldly up to the door and knocked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000896": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000896",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000897": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000897",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>A woman opened it just far enough to look out, and said, “What do you want, child, and why is that great Lion with you?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000898": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000898",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000899": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000899",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We wish to pass the night with you, if you will allow us,” answered Dorothy; “and the Lion is my friend and comrade, and would not hurt you for the world.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000900": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000900",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000901": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000901",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Is he tame?” asked the woman, opening the door a little wider.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000902": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000902",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000903": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000903",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, yes,” said the girl, “and he is a great coward, too. He will be more afraid of you than you are of him.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000904": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000904",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000905": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000905",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well,” said the woman, after thinking it over and taking another peep at the Lion, “if that is the case you may come in, and I will give you some supper and a place to sleep.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000906": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000906",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000907": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000907",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So they all entered the house, where there were, besides the woman, two children and a man. The man had hurt his leg, and was lying on the couch in a corner. They seemed greatly surprised to see so strange a company, and while the woman was busy laying the table the man asked:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000908": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000908",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000909": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000909",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Where are you all going?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000910": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000910",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000911": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000911",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“To the Emerald City,” said Dorothy, “to see the Great Oz.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000912": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000912",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000913": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000913",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, indeed!” exclaimed the man. “Are you sure that Oz will see you?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000914": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000914",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000915": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000915",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why not?” she replied.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000916": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000916",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000917": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000917",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why, it is said that he never lets anyone come into his presence. I have been to the Emerald City many times, and it is a beautiful and wonderful place; but I have never been permitted to see the Great Oz, nor do I know of any living person who has seen him.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000918": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000918",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000919": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000919",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Does he never go out?” asked the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000920": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000920",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000921": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000921",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Never. He sits day after day in the great Throne Room of his Palace, and even those who wait upon him do not see him face to face.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000922": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000922",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000923": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000923",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What is he like?” asked the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000924": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000924",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000925": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000925",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is hard to tell,” said the man thoughtfully. “You see, Oz is a Great Wizard, and can take on any form he wishes. So that some say he looks like a bird; and some say he looks like an elephant; and some say he looks like a cat. To others he appears as a beautiful fairy, or a brownie, or in any other form that pleases him. But who the real Oz is, when he is in his own form, no living person can tell.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000926": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000926",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000927": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000927",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is very strange,” said Dorothy, “but we must try, in some way, to see him, or we shall have made our journey for nothing.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000928": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000928",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000929": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000929",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why do you wish to see the terrible Oz?” asked the man.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000930": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000930",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000931": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000931",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I want him to give me some brains,” said the Scarecrow eagerly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000932": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000932",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000933": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000933",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, Oz could do that easily enough,” declared the man. “He has more brains than he needs.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000934": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000934",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000935": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000935",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I want him to give me a heart,” said the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000936": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000936",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000937": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000937",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That will not trouble him,” continued the man, “for Oz has a large collection of hearts, of all sizes and shapes.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000938": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000938",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000939": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000939",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I want him to give me courage,” said the Cowardly Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000940": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000940",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000941": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000941",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oz keeps a great pot of courage in his Throne Room,” said the man, “which he has covered with a golden plate, to keep it from running over. He will be glad to give you some.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000942": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000942",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000943": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000943",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I want him to send me back to Kansas,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000944": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000944",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000945": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000945",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Where is Kansas?” asked the man, with surprise.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000946": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000946",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000947": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000947",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I don’t know,” replied Dorothy sorrowfully, “but it is my home, and I’m sure it’s somewhere.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000948": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000948",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000949": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000949",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Very likely. Well, Oz can do anything; so I suppose he will find Kansas for you. But first you must get to see him, and that will be a hard task; for the Great Wizard does not like to see anyone, and he usually has his own way. But what do YOU want?” he continued, speaking to Toto. Toto only wagged his tail; for, strange to say, he could not speak.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000950": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000950",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000951": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000951",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The woman now called to them that supper was ready, so they gathered around the table and Dorothy ate some delicious porridge and a dish of scrambled eggs and a plate of nice white bread, and enjoyed her meal. The Lion ate some of the porridge, but did not care for it, saying it was made from oats and oats were food for horses, not for lions. The Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman ate nothing at all. Toto ate a little of everything, and was glad to get a good supper again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000952": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000952",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000953": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000953",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The woman now gave Dorothy a bed to sleep in, and Toto lay down beside her, while the Lion guarded the door of her room so she might not be disturbed. The Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman stood up in a corner and kept quiet all night, although of course they could not sleep.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000954": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000954",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000955": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000955",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The next morning, as soon as the sun was up, they started on their way, and soon saw a beautiful green glow in the sky just before them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000956": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000956",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000957": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000957",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That must be the Emerald City,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000958": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000958",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000959": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000959",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>As they walked on, the green glow became brighter and brighter, and it seemed that at last they were nearing the end of their travels. Yet it was afternoon before they came to the great wall that surrounded the City. It was high and thick and of a bright green color.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000960": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000960",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000961": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000961",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>In front of them, and at the end of the road of yellow brick, was a big gate, all studded with emeralds that glittered so in the sun that even the painted eyes of the Scarecrow were dazzled by their brilliancy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000962": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000962",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000963": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000963",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>There was a bell beside the gate, and Dorothy pushed the button and heard a silvery tinkle sound within. Then the big gate swung slowly open, and they all passed through and found themselves in a high arched room, the walls of which glistened with countless emeralds.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000964": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000964",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000965": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000965",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Before them stood a little man about the same size as the Munchkins. He was clothed all in green, from his head to his feet, and even his skin was of a greenish tint. At his side was a large green box.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000966": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000966",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000967": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000967",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When he saw Dorothy and her companions the man asked, “What do you wish in the Emerald City?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000968": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000968",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000969": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000969",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We came here to see the Great Oz,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000970": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000970",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000971": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000971",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The man was so surprised at this answer that he sat down to think it over.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000972": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000972",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000973": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000973",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It has been many years since anyone asked me to see Oz,” he said, shaking his head in perplexity. “He is powerful and terrible, and if you come on an idle or foolish errand to bother the wise reflections of the Great Wizard, he might be angry and destroy you all in an instant.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000974": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000974",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000975": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000975",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But it is not a foolish errand, nor an idle one,” replied the Scarecrow; “it is important. And we have been told that Oz is a good Wizard.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000976": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000976",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000977": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000977",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“So he is,” said the green man, “and he rules the Emerald City wisely and well. But to those who are not honest, or who approach him from curiosity, he is most terrible, and few have ever dared ask to see his face. I am the Guardian of the Gates, and since you demand to see the Great Oz I must take you to his Palace. But first you must put on the spectacles.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000978": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000978",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000979": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000979",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000980": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000980",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000981": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000981",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Because if you did not wear spectacles the brightness and glory of the Emerald City would blind you. Even those who live in the City must wear spectacles night and day. They are all locked on, for Oz so ordered it when the City was first built, and I have the only key that will unlock them.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000982": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000982",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000983": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000983",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>He opened the big box, and Dorothy saw that it was filled with spectacles of every size and shape. All of them had green glasses in them. The Guardian of the Gates found a pair that would just fit Dorothy and put them over her eyes. There were two golden bands fastened to them that passed around the back of her head, where they were locked together by a little key that was at the end of a chain the Guardian of the Gates wore around his neck. When they were on, Dorothy could not take them off had she wished, but of course she did not wish to be blinded by the glare of the Emerald City, so she said nothing.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000984": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000984",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000985": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000985",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then the green man fitted spectacles for the Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman and the Lion, and even on little Toto; and all were locked fast with the key.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000986": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000986",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000987": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000987",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then the Guardian of the Gates put on his own glasses and told them he was ready to show them to the Palace. Taking a big golden key from a peg on the wall, he opened another gate, and they all followed him through the portal into the streets of the Emerald City.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000988": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000988",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000989": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000989",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000990": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000990",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XI<br>\nThe Wonderful City of Oz</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000991": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000991",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000992": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000992",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Even with eyes protected by the green spectacles, Dorothy and her friends were at first dazzled by the brilliancy of the wonderful City. The streets were lined with beautiful houses all built of green marble and studded everywhere with sparkling emeralds. They walked over a pavement of the same green marble, and where the blocks were joined together were rows of emeralds, set closely, and glittering in the brightness of the sun. The window panes were of green glass; even the sky above the City had a green tint, and the rays of the sun were green.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000993": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000993",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000994": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000994",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>There were many people—men, women, and children—walking about, and these were all dressed in green clothes and had greenish skins. They looked at Dorothy and her strangely assorted company with wondering eyes, and the children all ran away and hid behind their mothers when they saw the Lion; but no one spoke to them. Many shops stood in the street, and Dorothy saw that everything in them was green. Green candy and green pop corn were offered for sale, as well as green shoes, green hats, and green clothes of all sorts. At one place a man was selling green lemonade, and when the children bought it Dorothy could see that they paid for it with green pennies.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000995": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000995",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000996": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000996",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>There seemed to be no horses nor animals of any kind; the men carried things around in little green carts, which they pushed before them. Everyone seemed happy and contented and prosperous.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000997": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000997",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000998": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000998",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Guardian of the Gates led them through the streets until they came to a big building, exactly in the middle of the City, which was the Palace of Oz, the Great Wizard. There was a soldier before the door, dressed in a green uniform and wearing a long green beard.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000999": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000000999",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001000": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001000",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Here are strangers,” said the Guardian of the Gates to him, “and they demand to see the Great Oz.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001001": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001001",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001002": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001002",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Step inside,” answered the soldier, “and I will carry your message to him.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001003": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001003",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001004": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001004",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So they passed through the Palace Gates and were led into a big room with a green carpet and lovely green furniture set with emeralds. The soldier made them all wipe their feet upon a green mat before entering this room, and when they were seated he said politely:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001005": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001005",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001006": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001006",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Please make yourselves comfortable while I go to the door of the Throne Room and tell Oz you are here.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001007": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001007",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001008": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001008",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They had to wait a long time before the soldier returned. When, at last, he came back, Dorothy asked:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001009": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001009",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001010": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001010",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Have you seen Oz?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001011": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001011",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001012": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001012",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, no,” returned the soldier; “I have never seen him. But I spoke to him as he sat behind his screen and gave him your message. He said he will grant you an audience, if you so desire; but each one of you must enter his presence alone, and he will admit but one each day. Therefore, as you must remain in the Palace for several days, I will have you shown to rooms where you may rest in comfort after your journey.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001013": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001013",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Thank you,” replied the girl; “that is very kind of Oz.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The soldier now blew upon a green whistle, and at once a young girl, dressed in a pretty green silk gown, entered the room. She had lovely green hair and green eyes, and she bowed low before Dorothy as she said, “Follow me and I will show you your room.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So Dorothy said good-bye to all her friends except Toto, and taking the dog in her arms followed the green girl through seven passages and up three flights of stairs until they came to a room at the front of the Palace. It was the sweetest little room in the world, with a soft comfortable bed that had sheets of green silk and a green velvet counterpane. There was a tiny fountain in the middle of the room, that shot a spray of green perfume into the air, to fall back into a beautifully carved green marble basin. Beautiful green flowers stood in the windows, and there was a shelf with a row of little green books. When Dorothy had time to open these books she found them full of queer green pictures that made her laugh, they were so funny.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>In a wardrobe were many green dresses, made of silk and satin and velvet; and all of them fitted Dorothy exactly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Make yourself perfectly at home,” said the green girl, “and if you wish for anything ring the bell. Oz will send for you tomorrow morning.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She left Dorothy alone and went back to the others. These she also led to rooms, and each one of them found himself lodged in a very pleasant part of the Palace. Of course this politeness was wasted on the Scarecrow; for when he found himself alone in his room he stood stupidly in one spot, just within the doorway, to wait till morning. It would not rest him to lie down, and he could not close his eyes; so he remained all night staring at a little spider which was weaving its web in a corner of the room, just as if it were not one of the most wonderful rooms in the world. The Tin Woodman lay down on his bed from force of habit, for he remembered when he was made of flesh; but not being able to sleep, he passed the night moving his joints up and down to make sure they kept in good working order. The Lion would have preferred a bed of dried leaves in the forest, and did not like being shut up in a room; but he had too much sense to let this worry him, so he sprang upon the bed and rolled himself up like a cat and purred himself asleep in a minute.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The next morning, after breakfast, the green maiden came to fetch Dorothy, and she dressed her in one of the prettiest gowns, made of green brocaded satin. Dorothy put on a green silk apron and tied a green ribbon around Toto’s neck, and they started for the Throne Room of the Great Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>First they came to a great hall in which were many ladies and gentlemen of the court, all dressed in rich costumes. These people had nothing to do but talk to each other, but they always came to wait outside the Throne Room every morning, although they were never permitted to see Oz. As Dorothy entered they looked at her curiously, and one of them whispered:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Are you really going to look upon the face of Oz the Terrible?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Of course,” answered the girl, “if he will see me.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, he will see you,” said the soldier who had taken her message to the Wizard, “although he does not like to have people ask to see him. Indeed, at first he was angry and said I should send you back where you came from. Then he asked me what you looked like, and when I mentioned your silver shoes he was very much interested. At last I told him about the mark upon your forehead, and he decided he would admit you to his presence.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Just then a bell rang, and the green girl said to Dorothy, “That is the signal. You must go into the Throne Room alone.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She opened a little door and Dorothy walked boldly through and found herself in a wonderful place. It was a big, round room with a high arched roof, and the walls and ceiling and floor were covered with large emeralds set closely together. In the center of the roof was a great light, as bright as the sun, which made the emeralds sparkle in a wonderful manner.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But what interested Dorothy most was the big throne of green marble that stood in the middle of the room. It was shaped like a chair and sparkled with gems, as did everything else. In the center of the chair was an enormous Head, without a body to support it or any arms or legs whatever. There was no hair upon this head, but it had eyes and a nose and mouth, and was much bigger than the head of the biggest giant.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>As Dorothy gazed upon this in wonder and fear, the eyes turned slowly and looked at her sharply and steadily. Then the mouth moved, and Dorothy heard a voice say:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001043": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001043",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001044": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001044",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am Oz, the Great and Terrible. Who are you, and why do you seek me?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001045": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001045",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001046": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001046",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>It was not such an awful voice as she had expected to come from the big Head; so she took courage and answered:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001047": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001047",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001048": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001048",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am Dorothy, the Small and Meek. I have come to you for help.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001049": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001049",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001050": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001050",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The eyes looked at her thoughtfully for a full minute. Then said the voice:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001051": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001051",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001052": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001052",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Where did you get the silver shoes?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001053": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001053",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001054": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001054",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I got them from the Wicked Witch of the East, when my house fell on her and killed her,” she replied.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001055": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001055",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001056": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001056",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Where did you get the mark upon your forehead?” continued the voice.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001057": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001057",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001058": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001058",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is where the Good Witch of the North kissed me when she bade me good-bye and sent me to you,” said the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001059": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001059",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001060": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001060",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Again the eyes looked at her sharply, and they saw she was telling the truth. Then Oz asked, “What do you wish me to do?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001061": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001061",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001062": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001062",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Send me back to Kansas, where my Aunt Em and Uncle Henry are,” she answered earnestly. “I don’t like your country, although it is so beautiful. And I am sure Aunt Em will be dreadfully worried over my being away so long.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001063": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001063",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001064": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001064",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The eyes winked three times, and then they turned up to the ceiling and down to the floor and rolled around so queerly that they seemed to see every part of the room. And at last they looked at Dorothy again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001065": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001065",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001066": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001066",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why should I do this for you?” asked Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001067": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001067",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001068": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001068",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Because you are strong and I am weak; because you are a Great Wizard and I am only a little girl.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001069": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001069",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001070": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001070",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But you were strong enough to kill the Wicked Witch of the East,” said Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001071": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001071",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001072": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001072",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That just happened,” returned Dorothy simply; “I could not help it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001073": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001073",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001074": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001074",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well,” said the Head, “I will give you my answer. You have no right to expect me to send you back to Kansas unless you do something for me in return. In this country everyone must pay for everything he gets. If you wish me to use my magic power to send you home again you must do something for me first. Help me and I will help you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001075": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001075",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001076": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001076",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What must I do?” asked the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001077": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001077",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001078": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001078",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Kill the Wicked Witch of the West,” answered Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001079": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001079",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001080": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001080",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But I cannot!” exclaimed Dorothy, greatly surprised.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001081": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001081",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001082": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001082",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You killed the Witch of the East and you wear the silver shoes, which bear a powerful charm. There is now but one Wicked Witch left in all this land, and when you can tell me she is dead I will send you back to Kansas—but not before.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001083": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001083",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001084": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001084",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The little girl began to weep, she was so much disappointed; and the eyes winked again and looked upon her anxiously, as if the Great Oz felt that she could help him if she would.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001085": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001085",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001086": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001086",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I never killed anything, willingly,” she sobbed. “Even if I wanted to, how could I kill the Wicked Witch? If you, who are Great and Terrible, cannot kill her yourself, how do you expect me to do it?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001087": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001087",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001088": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001088",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I do not know,” said the Head; “but that is my answer, and until the Wicked Witch dies you will not see your uncle and aunt again. Remember that the Witch is Wicked—tremendously Wicked—and ought to be killed. Now go, and do not ask to see me again until you have done your task.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001089": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001089",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001090": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001090",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Sorrowfully Dorothy left the Throne Room and went back where the Lion and the Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman were waiting to hear what Oz had said to her. “There is no hope for me,” she said sadly, “for Oz will not send me home until I have killed the Wicked Witch of the West; and that I can never do.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001091": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001091",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001092": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001092",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Her friends were sorry, but could do nothing to help her; so Dorothy went to her own room and lay down on the bed and cried herself to sleep.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001093": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001093",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001094": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001094",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The next morning the soldier with the green whiskers came to the Scarecrow and said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001095": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001095",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001096": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001096",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come with me, for Oz has sent for you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001097": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001097",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001098": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001098",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Scarecrow followed him and was admitted into the great Throne Room, where he saw, sitting in the emerald throne, a most lovely Lady. She was dressed in green silk gauze and wore upon her flowing green locks a crown of jewels. Growing from her shoulders were wings, gorgeous in color and so light that they fluttered if the slightest breath of air reached them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001099": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001099",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001100": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001100",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When the Scarecrow had bowed, as prettily as his straw stuffing would let him, before this beautiful creature, she looked upon him sweetly, and said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001101": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001101",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001102": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001102",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am Oz, the Great and Terrible. Who are you, and why do you seek me?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001103": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001103",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001104": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001104",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Now the Scarecrow, who had expected to see the great Head Dorothy had told him of, was much astonished; but he answered her bravely.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001105": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001105",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001106": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001106",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am only a Scarecrow, stuffed with straw. Therefore I have no brains, and I come to you praying that you will put brains in my head instead of straw, so that I may become as much a man as any other in your dominions.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001107": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001107",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001108": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001108",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why should I do this for you?” asked the Lady.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001109": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001109",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001110": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001110",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Because you are wise and powerful, and no one else can help me,” answered the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001111": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001111",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001112": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001112",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I never grant favors without some return,” said Oz; “but this much I will promise. If you will kill for me the Wicked Witch of the West, I will bestow upon you a great many brains, and such good brains that you will be the wisest man in all the Land of Oz.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001113": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001113",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001114": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001114",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I thought you asked Dorothy to kill the Witch,” said the Scarecrow, in surprise.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001115": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001115",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001116": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001116",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“So I did. I don’t care who kills her. But until she is dead I will not grant your wish. Now go, and do not seek me again until you have earned the brains you so greatly desire.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001117": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001117",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001118": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001118",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow went sorrowfully back to his friends and told them what Oz had said; and Dorothy was surprised to find that the Great Wizard was not a Head, as she had seen him, but a lovely Lady.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001119": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001119",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001120": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001120",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“All the same,” said the Scarecrow, “she needs a heart as much as the Tin Woodman.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001121": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001121",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001122": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001122",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>On the next morning the soldier with the green whiskers came to the Tin Woodman and said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001123": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001123",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001124": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001124",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oz has sent for you. Follow me.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001125": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001125",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001126": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001126",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Tin Woodman followed him and came to the great Throne Room. He did not know whether he would find Oz a lovely Lady or a Head, but he hoped it would be the lovely Lady. “For,” he said to himself, “if it is the head, I am sure I shall not be given a heart, since a head has no heart of its own and therefore cannot feel for me. But if it is the lovely Lady I shall beg hard for a heart, for all ladies are themselves said to be kindly hearted.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001127": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001127",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001128": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001128",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But when the Woodman entered the great Throne Room he saw neither the Head nor the Lady, for Oz had taken the shape of a most terrible Beast. It was nearly as big as an elephant, and the green throne seemed hardly strong enough to hold its weight. The Beast had a head like that of a rhinoceros, only there were five eyes in its face. There were five long arms growing out of its body, and it also had five long, slim legs. Thick, woolly hair covered every part of it, and a more dreadful-looking monster could not be imagined. It was fortunate the Tin Woodman had no heart at that moment, for it would have beat loud and fast from terror. But being only tin, the Woodman was not at all afraid, although he was much disappointed.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001129": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001129",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001130": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001130",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am Oz, the Great and Terrible,” spoke the Beast, in a voice that was one great roar. “Who are you, and why do you seek me?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001131": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001131",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001132": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001132",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am a Woodman, and made of tin. Therefore I have no heart, and cannot love. I pray you to give me a heart that I may be as other men are.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001133": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001133",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001134": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001134",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why should I do this?” demanded the Beast.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001135": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001135",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001136": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001136",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Because I ask it, and you alone can grant my request,” answered the Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001137": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001137",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001138": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001138",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Oz gave a low growl at this, but said, gruffly: “If you indeed desire a heart, you must earn it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001139": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001139",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001140": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001140",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How?” asked the Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001141": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001141",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001142": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001142",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Help Dorothy to kill the Wicked Witch of the West,” replied the Beast. “When the Witch is dead, come to me, and I will then give you the biggest and kindest and most loving heart in all the Land of Oz.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001143": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001143",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001144": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001144",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Tin Woodman was forced to return sorrowfully to his friends and tell them of the terrible Beast he had seen. They all wondered greatly at the many forms the Great Wizard could take upon himself, and the Lion said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001145": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001145",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001146": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001146",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If he is a Beast when I go to see him, I shall roar my loudest, and so frighten him that he will grant all I ask. And if he is the lovely Lady, I shall pretend to spring upon her, and so compel her to do my bidding. And if he is the great Head, he will be at my mercy; for I will roll this head all about the room until he promises to give us what we desire. So be of good cheer, my friends, for all will yet be well.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001147": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001147",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001148": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001148",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The next morning the soldier with the green whiskers led the Lion to the great Throne Room and bade him enter the presence of Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001149": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001149",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001150": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001150",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion at once passed through the door, and glancing around saw, to his surprise, that before the throne was a Ball of Fire, so fierce and glowing he could scarcely bear to gaze upon it. His first thought was that Oz had by accident caught on fire and was burning up; but when he tried to go nearer, the heat was so intense that it singed his whiskers, and he crept back tremblingly to a spot nearer the door.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001151": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001151",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001152": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001152",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then a low, quiet voice came from the Ball of Fire, and these were the words it spoke:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001153": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001153",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001154": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001154",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am Oz, the Great and Terrible. Who are you, and why do you seek me?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001155": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001155",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001156": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001156",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>And the Lion answered, “I am a Cowardly Lion, afraid of everything. I came to you to beg that you give me courage, so that in reality I may become the King of Beasts, as men call me.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001157": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001157",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why should I give you courage?” demanded Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Because of all Wizards you are the greatest, and alone have power to grant my request,” answered the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Ball of Fire burned fiercely for a time, and the voice said, “Bring me proof that the Wicked Witch is dead, and that moment I will give you courage. But as long as the Witch lives, you must remain a coward.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion was angry at this speech, but could say nothing in reply, and while he stood silently gazing at the Ball of Fire it became so furiously hot that he turned tail and rushed from the room. He was glad to find his friends waiting for him, and told them of his terrible interview with the Wizard.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001165",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001166": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001166",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What shall we do now?” asked Dorothy sadly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001167": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001167",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001168": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001168",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“There is only one thing we can do,” returned the Lion, “and that is to go to the land of the Winkies, seek out the Wicked Witch, and destroy her.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001169": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001169",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001170": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001170",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But suppose we cannot?” said the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001171": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001171",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001172": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001172",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Then I shall never have courage,” declared the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001173": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001173",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001174": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001174",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I shall never have brains,” added the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001175": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001175",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001176": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001176",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I shall never have a heart,” spoke the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001177": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001177",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001178": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001178",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I shall never see Aunt Em and Uncle Henry,” said Dorothy, beginning to cry.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001179": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001179",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001180": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001180",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Be careful!” cried the green girl. “The tears will fall on your green silk gown and spot it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001181": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001181",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001182": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001182",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So Dorothy dried her eyes and said, “I suppose we must try it; but I am sure I do not want to kill anybody, even to see Aunt Em again.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001183": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001183",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001184": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001184",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I will go with you; but I’m too much of a coward to kill the Witch,” said the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001185": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001185",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001186": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001186",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I will go too,” declared the Scarecrow; “but I shall not be of much help to you, I am such a fool.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001187": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001187",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001188": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001188",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I haven’t the heart to harm even a Witch,” remarked the Tin Woodman; “but if you go I certainly shall go with you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001189": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001189",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001190": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001190",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Therefore it was decided to start upon their journey the next morning, and the Woodman sharpened his axe on a green grindstone and had all his joints properly oiled. The Scarecrow stuffed himself with fresh straw and Dorothy put new paint on his eyes that he might see better. The green girl, who was very kind to them, filled Dorothy’s basket with good things to eat, and fastened a little bell around Toto’s neck with a green ribbon.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001191": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001191",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001192": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001192",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They went to bed quite early and slept soundly until daylight, when they were awakened by the crowing of a green cock that lived in the back yard of the Palace, and the cackling of a hen that had laid a green egg.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001193": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001193",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001194": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001194",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001195": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001195",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XII<br>\nThe Search for the Wicked Witch</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001196": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001196",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001197": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001197",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The soldier with the green whiskers led them through the streets of the Emerald City until they reached the room where the Guardian of the Gates lived. This officer unlocked their spectacles to put them back in his great box, and then he politely opened the gate for our friends.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001198": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001198",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001199": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001199",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Which road leads to the Wicked Witch of the West?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001200": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001200",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001201": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001201",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“There is no road,” answered the Guardian of the Gates. “No one ever wishes to go that way.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001202": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001202",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001203": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001203",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How, then, are we to find her?” inquired the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001204": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001204",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001205": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001205",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That will be easy,” replied the man, “for when she knows you are in the country of the Winkies she will find you, and make you all her slaves.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001206": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001206",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001207": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001207",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Perhaps not,” said the Scarecrow, “for we mean to destroy her.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001208": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001208",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001209": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001209",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, that is different,” said the Guardian of the Gates. “No one has ever destroyed her before, so I naturally thought she would make slaves of you, as she has of the rest. But take care; for she is wicked and fierce, and may not allow you to destroy her. Keep to the West, where the sun sets, and you cannot fail to find her.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001210": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001210",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001211": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001211",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They thanked him and bade him good-bye, and turned toward the West, walking over fields of soft grass dotted here and there with daisies and buttercups. Dorothy still wore the pretty silk dress she had put on in the palace, but now, to her surprise, she found it was no longer green, but pure white. The ribbon around Toto’s neck had also lost its green color and was as white as Dorothy’s dress.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001212": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001212",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001213": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001213",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Emerald City was soon left far behind. As they advanced the ground became rougher and hillier, for there were no farms nor houses in this country of the West, and the ground was untilled.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001214": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001214",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001215": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001215",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>In the afternoon the sun shone hot in their faces, for there were no trees to offer them shade; so that before night Dorothy and Toto and the Lion were tired, and lay down upon the grass and fell asleep, with the Woodman and the Scarecrow keeping watch.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001216": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001216",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001217": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001217",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Now the Wicked Witch of the West had but one eye, yet that was as powerful as a telescope, and could see everywhere. So, as she sat in the door of her castle, she happened to look around and saw Dorothy lying asleep, with her friends all about her. They were a long distance off, but the Wicked Witch was angry to find them in her country; so she blew upon a silver whistle that hung around her neck.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001218": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001218",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001219": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001219",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>At once there came running to her from all directions a pack of great wolves. They had long legs and fierce eyes and sharp teeth.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001220": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001220",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001221": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001221",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Go to those people,” said the Witch, “and tear them to pieces.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001222": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001222",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001223": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001223",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Are you not going to make them your slaves?” asked the leader of the wolves.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001224": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001224",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001225": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001225",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No,” she answered, “one is of tin, and one of straw; one is a girl and another a Lion. None of them is fit to work, so you may tear them into small pieces.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001226": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001226",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001227": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001227",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Very well,” said the wolf, and he dashed away at full speed, followed by the others.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>It was lucky the Scarecrow and the Woodman were wide awake and heard the wolves coming.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This is my fight,” said the Woodman, “so get behind me and I will meet them as they come.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>He seized his axe, which he had made very sharp, and as the leader of the wolves came on the Tin Woodman swung his arm and chopped the wolf’s head from its body, so that it immediately died. As soon as he could raise his axe another wolf came up, and he also fell under the sharp edge of the Tin Woodman’s weapon. There were forty wolves, and forty times a wolf was killed, so that at last they all lay dead in a heap before the Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then he put down his axe and sat beside the Scarecrow, who said, “It was a good fight, friend.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They waited until Dorothy awoke the next morning. The little girl was quite frightened when she saw the great pile of shaggy wolves, but the Tin Woodman told her all. She thanked him for saving them and sat down to breakfast, after which they started again upon their journey.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Now this same morning the Wicked Witch came to the door of her castle and looked out with her one eye that could see far off. She saw all her wolves lying dead, and the strangers still traveling through her country. This made her angrier than before, and she blew her silver whistle twice.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Straightway a great flock of wild crows came flying toward her, enough to darken the sky.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>And the Wicked Witch said to the King Crow, “Fly at once to the strangers; peck out their eyes and tear them to pieces.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The wild crows flew in one great flock toward Dorothy and her companions. When the little girl saw them coming she was afraid.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the Scarecrow said, “This is my battle, so lie down beside me and you will not be harmed.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So they all lay upon the ground except the Scarecrow, and he stood up and stretched out his arms. And when the crows saw him they were frightened, as these birds always are by scarecrows, and did not dare to come any nearer. But the King Crow said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It is only a stuffed man. I will peck his eyes out.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The King Crow flew at the Scarecrow, who caught it by the head and twisted its neck until it died. And then another crow flew at him, and the Scarecrow twisted its neck also. There were forty crows, and forty times the Scarecrow twisted a neck, until at last all were lying dead beside him. Then he called to his companions to rise, and again they went upon their journey.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When the Wicked Witch looked out again and saw all her crows lying in a heap, she got into a terrible rage, and blew three times upon her silver whistle.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Forthwith there was heard a great buzzing in the air, and a swarm of black bees came flying toward her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Go to the strangers and sting them to death!” commanded the Witch, and the bees turned and flew rapidly until they came to where Dorothy and her friends were walking. But the Woodman had seen them coming, and the Scarecrow had decided what to do.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Take out my straw and scatter it over the little girl and the dog and the Lion,” he said to the Woodman, “and the bees cannot sting them.” This the Woodman did, and as Dorothy lay close beside the Lion and held Toto in her arms, the straw covered them entirely.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The bees came and found no one but the Woodman to sting, so they flew at him and broke off all their stings against the tin, without hurting the Woodman at all. And as bees cannot live when their stings are broken that was the end of the black bees, and they lay scattered thick about the Woodman, like little heaps of fine coal.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then Dorothy and the Lion got up, and the girl helped the Tin Woodman put the straw back into the Scarecrow again, until he was as good as ever. So they started upon their journey once more.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Wicked Witch was so angry when she saw her black bees in little heaps like fine coal that she stamped her foot and tore her hair and gnashed her teeth. And then she called a dozen of her slaves, who were the Winkies, and gave them sharp spears, telling them to go to the strangers and destroy them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Winkies were not a brave people, but they had to do as they were told. So they marched away until they came near to Dorothy. Then the Lion gave a great roar and sprang towards them, and the poor Winkies were so frightened that they ran back as fast as they could.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When they returned to the castle the Wicked Witch beat them well with a strap, and sent them back to their work, after which she sat down to think what she should do next. She could not understand how all her plans to destroy these strangers had failed; but she was a powerful Witch, as well as a wicked one, and she soon made up her mind how to act.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>There was, in her cupboard, a Golden Cap, with a circle of diamonds and rubies running round it. This Golden Cap had a charm. Whoever owned it could call three times upon the Winged Monkeys, who would obey any order they were given. But no person could command these strange creatures more than three times. Twice already the Wicked Witch had used the charm of the Cap. Once was when she had made the Winkies her slaves, and set herself to rule over their country. The Winged Monkeys had helped her do this. The second time was when she had fought against the Great Oz himself, and driven him out of the land of the West. The Winged Monkeys had also helped her in doing this. Only once more could she use this Golden Cap, for which reason she did not like to do so until all her other powers were exhausted. But now that her fierce wolves and her wild crows and her stinging bees were gone, and her slaves had been scared away by the Cowardly Lion, she saw there was only one way left to destroy Dorothy and her friends.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Wicked Witch took the Golden Cap from her cupboard and placed it upon her head. Then she stood upon her left foot and said slowly:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Ep-pe, pep-pe, kak-ke!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Next she stood upon her right foot and said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Hil-lo, hol-lo, hel-lo!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>After this she stood upon both feet and cried in a loud voice:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Ziz-zy, zuz-zy, zik!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Now the charm began to work. The sky was darkened, and a low rumbling sound was heard in the air. There was a rushing of many wings, a great chattering and laughing, and the sun came out of the dark sky to show the Wicked Witch surrounded by a crowd of monkeys, each with a pair of immense and powerful wings on his shoulders.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>One, much bigger than the others, seemed to be their leader. He flew close to the Witch and said, “You have called us for the third and last time. What do you command?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Go to the strangers who are within my land and destroy them all except the Lion,” said the Wicked Witch. “Bring that beast to me, for I have a mind to harness him like a horse, and make him work.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Your commands shall be obeyed,” said the leader. Then, with a great deal of chattering and noise, the Winged Monkeys flew away to the place where Dorothy and her friends were walking.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Some of the Monkeys seized the Tin Woodman and carried him through the air until they were over a country thickly covered with sharp rocks. Here they dropped the poor Woodman, who fell a great distance to the rocks, where he lay so battered and dented that he could neither move nor groan.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Others of the Monkeys caught the Scarecrow, and with their long fingers pulled all of the straw out of his clothes and head. They made his hat and boots and clothes into a small bundle and threw it into the top branches of a tall tree.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The remaining Monkeys threw pieces of stout rope around the Lion and wound many coils about his body and head and legs, until he was unable to bite or scratch or struggle in any way. Then they lifted him up and flew away with him to the Witch’s castle, where he was placed in a small yard with a high iron fence around it, so that he could not escape.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But Dorothy they did not harm at all. She stood, with Toto in her arms, watching the sad fate of her comrades and thinking it would soon be her turn. The leader of the Winged Monkeys flew up to her, his long, hairy arms stretched out and his ugly face grinning terribly; but he saw the mark of the Good Witch’s kiss upon her forehead and stopped short, motioning the others not to touch her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We dare not harm this little girl,” he said to them, “for she is protected by the Power of Good, and that is greater than the Power of Evil. All we can do is to carry her to the castle of the Wicked Witch and leave her there.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So, carefully and gently, they lifted Dorothy in their arms and carried her swiftly through the air until they came to the castle, where they set her down upon the front doorstep. Then the leader said to the Witch:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001307": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001307",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We have obeyed you as far as we were able. The Tin Woodman and the Scarecrow are destroyed, and the Lion is tied up in your yard. The little girl we dare not harm, nor the dog she carries in her arms. Your power over our band is now ended, and you will never see us again.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001308": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001308",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then all the Winged Monkeys, with much laughing and chattering and noise, flew into the air and were soon out of sight.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Wicked Witch was both surprised and worried when she saw the mark on Dorothy’s forehead, for she knew well that neither the Winged Monkeys nor she, herself, dare hurt the girl in any way. She looked down at Dorothy’s feet, and seeing the Silver Shoes, began to tremble with fear, for she knew what a powerful charm belonged to them. At first the Witch was tempted to run away from Dorothy; but she happened to look into the child’s eyes and saw how simple the soul behind them was, and that the little girl did not know of the wonderful power the Silver Shoes gave her. So the Wicked Witch laughed to herself, and thought, “I can still make her my slave, for she does not know how to use her power.” Then she said to Dorothy, harshly and severely:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come with me; and see that you mind everything I tell you, for if you do not I will make an end of you, as I did of the Tin Woodman and the Scarecrow.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy followed her through many of the beautiful rooms in her castle until they came to the kitchen, where the Witch bade her clean the pots and kettles and sweep the floor and keep the fire fed with wood.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy went to work meekly, with her mind made up to work as hard as she could; for she was glad the Wicked Witch had decided not to kill her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>With Dorothy hard at work, the Witch thought she would go into the courtyard and harness the Cowardly Lion like a horse; it would amuse her, she was sure, to make him draw her chariot whenever she wished to go to drive. But as she opened the gate the Lion gave a loud roar and bounded at her so fiercely that the Witch was afraid, and ran out and shut the gate again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If I cannot harness you,” said the Witch to the Lion, speaking through the bars of the gate, “I can starve you. You shall have nothing to eat until you do as I wish.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So after that she took no food to the imprisoned Lion; but every day she came to the gate at noon and asked, “Are you ready to be harnessed like a horse?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>And the Lion would answer, “No. If you come in this yard, I will bite you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The reason the Lion did not have to do as the Witch wished was that every night, while the woman was asleep, Dorothy carried him food from the cupboard. After he had eaten he would lie down on his bed of straw, and Dorothy would lie beside him and put her head on his soft, shaggy mane, while they talked of their troubles and tried to plan some way to escape. But they could find no way to get out of the castle, for it was constantly guarded by the yellow Winkies, who were the slaves of the Wicked Witch and too afraid of her not to do as she told them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The girl had to work hard during the day, and often the Witch threatened to beat her with the same old umbrella she always carried in her hand. But, in truth, she did not dare to strike Dorothy, because of the mark upon her forehead. The child did not know this, and was full of fear for herself and Toto. Once the Witch struck Toto a blow with her umbrella and the brave little dog flew at her and bit her leg in return. The Witch did not bleed where she was bitten, for she was so wicked that the blood in her had dried up many years before.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy’s life became very sad as she grew to understand that it would be harder than ever to get back to Kansas and Aunt Em again. Sometimes she would cry bitterly for hours, with Toto sitting at her feet and looking into her face, whining dismally to show how sorry he was for his little mistress. Toto did not really care whether he was in Kansas or the Land of Oz so long as Dorothy was with him; but he knew the little girl was unhappy, and that made him unhappy too.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Now the Wicked Witch had a great longing to have for her own the Silver Shoes which the girl always wore. Her bees and her crows and her wolves were lying in heaps and drying up, and she had used up all the power of the Golden Cap; but if she could only get hold of the Silver Shoes, they would give her more power than all the other things she had lost. She watched Dorothy carefully, to see if she ever took off her shoes, thinking she might steal them. But the child was so proud of her pretty shoes that she never took them off except at night and when she took her bath. The Witch was too much afraid of the dark to dare go in Dorothy’s room at night to take the shoes, and her dread of water was greater than her fear of the dark, so she never came near when Dorothy was bathing. Indeed, the old Witch never touched water, nor ever let water touch her in any way.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the wicked creature was very cunning, and she finally thought of a trick that would give her what she wanted. She placed a bar of iron in the middle of the kitchen floor, and then by her magic arts made the iron invisible to human eyes. So that when Dorothy walked across the floor she stumbled over the bar, not being able to see it, and fell at full length. She was not much hurt, but in her fall one of the Silver Shoes came off; and before she could reach it, the Witch had snatched it away and put it on her own skinny foot.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The wicked woman was greatly pleased with the success of her trick, for as long as she had one of the shoes she owned half the power of their charm, and Dorothy could not use it against her, even had she known how to do so.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The little girl, seeing she had lost one of her pretty shoes, grew angry, and said to the Witch, “Give me back my shoe!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I will not,” retorted the Witch, “for it is now my shoe, and not yours.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You are a wicked creature!” cried Dorothy. “You have no right to take my shoe from me.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I shall keep it, just the same,” said the Witch, laughing at her, “and someday I shall get the other one from you, too.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>This made Dorothy so very angry that she picked up the bucket of water that stood near and dashed it over the Witch, wetting her from head to foot.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Instantly the wicked woman gave a loud cry of fear, and then, as Dorothy looked at her in wonder, the Witch began to shrink and fall away.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“See what you have done!” she screamed. “In a minute I shall melt away.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I’m very sorry, indeed,” said Dorothy, who was truly frightened to see the Witch actually melting away like brown sugar before her very eyes.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Didn’t you know water would be the end of me?” asked the Witch, in a wailing, despairing voice.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Of course not,” answered Dorothy. “How should I?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well, in a few minutes I shall be all melted, and you will have the castle to yourself. I have been wicked in my day, but I never thought a little girl like you would ever be able to melt me and end my wicked deeds. Look out—here I go!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>With these words the Witch fell down in a brown, melted, shapeless mass and began to spread over the clean boards of the kitchen floor. Seeing that she had really melted away to nothing, Dorothy drew another bucket of water and threw it over the mess. She then swept it all out the door. After picking out the silver shoe, which was all that was left of the old woman, she cleaned and dried it with a cloth, and put it on her foot again. Then, being at last free to do as she chose, she ran out to the courtyard to tell the Lion that the Wicked Witch of the West had come to an end, and that they were no longer prisoners in a strange land.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XIII<br>\nThe Rescue</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Cowardly Lion was much pleased to hear that the Wicked Witch had been melted by a bucket of water, and Dorothy at once unlocked the gate of his prison and set him free. They went in together to the castle, where Dorothy’s first act was to call all the Winkies together and tell them that they were no longer slaves.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>There was great rejoicing among the yellow Winkies, for they had been made to work hard during many years for the Wicked Witch, who had always treated them with great cruelty. They kept this day as a holiday, then and ever after, and spent the time in feasting and dancing.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If our friends, the Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman, were only with us,” said the Lion, “I should be quite happy.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Don’t you suppose we could rescue them?” asked the girl anxiously.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We can try,” answered the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So they called the yellow Winkies and asked them if they would help to rescue their friends, and the Winkies said that they would be delighted to do all in their power for Dorothy, who had set them free from bondage. So she chose a number of the Winkies who looked as if they knew the most, and they all started away. They traveled that day and part of the next until they came to the rocky plain where the Tin Woodman lay, all battered and bent. His axe was near him, but the blade was rusted and the handle broken off short.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Winkies lifted him tenderly in their arms, and carried him back to the Yellow Castle again, Dorothy shedding a few tears by the way at the sad plight of her old friend, and the Lion looking sober and sorry. When they reached the castle Dorothy said to the Winkies:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Are any of your people tinsmiths?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, yes. Some of us are very good tinsmiths,” they told her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001383": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001383",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001384": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001384",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Then bring them to me,” she said. And when the tinsmiths came, bringing with them all their tools in baskets, she inquired, “Can you straighten out those dents in the Tin Woodman, and bend him back into shape again, and solder him together where he is broken?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001385": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001385",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001386": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001386",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The tinsmiths looked the Woodman over carefully and then answered that they thought they could mend him so he would be as good as ever. So they set to work in one of the big yellow rooms of the castle and worked for three days and four nights, hammering and twisting and bending and soldering and polishing and pounding at the legs and body and head of the Tin Woodman, until at last he was straightened out into his old form, and his joints worked as well as ever. To be sure, there were several patches on him, but the tinsmiths did a good job, and as the Woodman was not a vain man he did not mind the patches at all.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001387": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001387",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001388": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001388",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When, at last, he walked into Dorothy’s room and thanked her for rescuing him, he was so pleased that he wept tears of joy, and Dorothy had to wipe every tear carefully from his face with her apron, so his joints would not be rusted. At the same time her own tears fell thick and fast at the joy of meeting her old friend again, and these tears did not need to be wiped away. As for the Lion, he wiped his eyes so often with the tip of his tail that it became quite wet, and he was obliged to go out into the courtyard and hold it in the sun till it dried.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001389": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001389",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001390": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001390",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If we only had the Scarecrow with us again,” said the Tin Woodman, when Dorothy had finished telling him everything that had happened, “I should be quite happy.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001391": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001391",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001392": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001392",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We must try to find him,” said the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001393": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001393",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001394": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001394",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So she called the Winkies to help her, and they walked all that day and part of the next until they came to the tall tree in the branches of which the Winged Monkeys had tossed the Scarecrow’s clothes.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001395": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001395",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001396": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001396",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>It was a very tall tree, and the trunk was so smooth that no one could climb it; but the Woodman said at once, “I’ll chop it down, and then we can get the Scarecrow’s clothes.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001397": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001397",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001398": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001398",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Now while the tinsmiths had been at work mending the Woodman himself, another of the Winkies, who was a goldsmith, had made an axe-handle of solid gold and fitted it to the Woodman’s axe, instead of the old broken handle. Others polished the blade until all the rust was removed and it glistened like burnished silver.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001399": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001399",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001400": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001400",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>As soon as he had spoken, the Tin Woodman began to chop, and in a short time the tree fell over with a crash, whereupon the Scarecrow’s clothes fell out of the branches and rolled off on the ground.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001401": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001401",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001402": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001402",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy picked them up and had the Winkies carry them back to the castle, where they were stuffed with nice, clean straw; and behold! here was the Scarecrow, as good as ever, thanking them over and over again for saving him.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001403": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001403",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001404": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001404",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Now that they were reunited, Dorothy and her friends spent a few happy days at the Yellow Castle, where they found everything they needed to make them comfortable.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001405": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001405",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001406": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001406",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But one day the girl thought of Aunt Em, and said, “We must go back to Oz, and claim his promise.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001407": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001407",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001408": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001408",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yes,” said the Woodman, “at last I shall get my heart.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001409": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001409",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001410": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001410",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I shall get my brains,” added the Scarecrow joyfully.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001411": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001411",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001412": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001412",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I shall get my courage,” said the Lion thoughtfully.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001413": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001413",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001414": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001414",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I shall get back to Kansas,” cried Dorothy, clapping her hands. “Oh, let us start for the Emerald City tomorrow!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001415": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001415",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001416": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001416",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>This they decided to do. The next day they called the Winkies together and bade them good-bye. The Winkies were sorry to have them go, and they had grown so fond of the Tin Woodman that they begged him to stay and rule over them and the Yellow Land of the West. Finding they were determined to go, the Winkies gave Toto and the Lion each a golden collar; and to Dorothy they presented a beautiful bracelet studded with diamonds; and to the Scarecrow they gave a gold-headed walking stick, to keep him from stumbling; and to the Tin Woodman they offered a silver oil-can, inlaid with gold and set with precious jewels.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001417": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001417",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001418": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001418",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Every one of the travelers made the Winkies a pretty speech in return, and all shook hands with them until their arms ached.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001419": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001419",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001420": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001420",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy went to the Witch’s cupboard to fill her basket with food for the journey, and there she saw the Golden Cap. She tried it on her own head and found that it fitted her exactly. She did not know anything about the charm of the Golden Cap, but she saw that it was pretty, so she made up her mind to wear it and carry her sunbonnet in the basket.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001421": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001421",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001422": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001422",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then, being prepared for the journey, they all started for the Emerald City; and the Winkies gave them three cheers and many good wishes to carry with them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001423": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001423",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001424": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001424",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001425": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001425",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XIV<br>\nThe Winged Monkeys</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001426": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001426",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001427": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001427",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>You will remember there was no road—not even a pathway—between the castle of the Wicked Witch and the Emerald City. When the four travelers went in search of the Witch she had seen them coming, and so sent the Winged Monkeys to bring them to her. It was much harder to find their way back through the big fields of buttercups and yellow daisies than it was being carried. They knew, of course, they must go straight east, toward the rising sun; and they started off in the right way. But at noon, when the sun was over their heads, they did not know which was east and which was west, and that was the reason they were lost in the great fields. They kept on walking, however, and at night the moon came out and shone brightly. So they lay down among the sweet smelling yellow flowers and slept soundly until morning—all but the Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001428": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001428",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001429": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001429",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The next morning the sun was behind a cloud, but they started on, as if they were quite sure which way they were going.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001430": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001430",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001431": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001431",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If we walk far enough,” said Dorothy, “I am sure we shall sometime come to some place.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001432": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001432",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001433": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001433",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But day by day passed away, and they still saw nothing before them but the scarlet fields. The Scarecrow began to grumble a bit.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001434": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001434",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001435": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001435",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We have surely lost our way,” he said, “and unless we find it again in time to reach the Emerald City, I shall never get my brains.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001436": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001436",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001437": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001437",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Nor I my heart,” declared the Tin Woodman. “It seems to me I can scarcely wait till I get to Oz, and you must admit this is a very long journey.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001438": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001438",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001439": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001439",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You see,” said the Cowardly Lion, with a whimper, “I haven’t the courage to keep tramping forever, without getting anywhere at all.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001440": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001440",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001441": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001441",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then Dorothy lost heart. She sat down on the grass and looked at her companions, and they sat down and looked at her, and Toto found that for the first time in his life he was too tired to chase a butterfly that flew past his head. So he put out his tongue and panted and looked at Dorothy as if to ask what they should do next.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001442": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001442",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001443": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001443",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Suppose we call the field mice,” she suggested. “They could probably tell us the way to the Emerald City.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001444": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001444",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001445": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001445",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“To be sure they could,” cried the Scarecrow. “Why didn’t we think of that before?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001446": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001446",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001447": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001447",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy blew the little whistle she had always carried about her neck since the Queen of the Mice had given it to her. In a few minutes they heard the pattering of tiny feet, and many of the small gray mice came running up to her. Among them was the Queen herself, who asked, in her squeaky little voice:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001448": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001448",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001449": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001449",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What can I do for my friends?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001450": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001450",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001451": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001451",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We have lost our way,” said Dorothy. “Can you tell us where the Emerald City is?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001452": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001452",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001453": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001453",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Certainly,” answered the Queen; “but it is a great way off, for you have had it at your backs all this time.” Then she noticed Dorothy’s Golden Cap, and said, “Why don’t you use the charm of the Cap, and call the Winged Monkeys to you? They will carry you to the City of Oz in less than an hour.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001454": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001454",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001455": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001455",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I didn’t know there was a charm,” answered Dorothy, in surprise. “What is it?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001456": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001456",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001457": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001457",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It is written inside the Golden Cap,” replied the Queen of the Mice. “But if you are going to call the Winged Monkeys we must run away, for they are full of mischief and think it great fun to plague us.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001458": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001458",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001459": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001459",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Won’t they hurt me?” asked the girl anxiously.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001460": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001460",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001461": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001461",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, no. They must obey the wearer of the Cap. Good-bye!” And she scampered out of sight, with all the mice hurrying after her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001462": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001462",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001463": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001463",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy looked inside the Golden Cap and saw some words written upon the lining. These, she thought, must be the charm, so she read the directions carefully and put the Cap upon her head.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001464": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001464",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001465": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001465",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Ep-pe, pep-pe, kak-ke!” she said, standing on her left foot.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001466": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001466",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001467": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001467",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What did you say?” asked the Scarecrow, who did not know what she was doing.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001468": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001468",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001469": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001469",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Hil-lo, hol-lo, hel-lo!” Dorothy went on, standing this time on her right foot.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001470": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001470",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001471": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001471",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Hello!” replied the Tin Woodman calmly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001472": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001472",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001473": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001473",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Ziz-zy, zuz-zy, zik!” said Dorothy, who was now standing on both feet. This ended the saying of the charm, and they heard a great chattering and flapping of wings, as the band of Winged Monkeys flew up to them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001474": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001474",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001475": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001475",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The King bowed low before Dorothy, and asked, “What is your command?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001476": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001476",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001477": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001477",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We wish to go to the Emerald City,” said the child, “and we have lost our way.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001478": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001478",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001479": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001479",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We will carry you,” replied the King, and no sooner had he spoken than two of the Monkeys caught Dorothy in their arms and flew away with her. Others took the Scarecrow and the Woodman and the Lion, and one little Monkey seized Toto and flew after them, although the dog tried hard to bite him.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001480": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001480",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001481": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001481",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman were rather frightened at first, for they remembered how badly the Winged Monkeys had treated them before; but they saw that no harm was intended, so they rode through the air quite cheerfully, and had a fine time looking at the pretty gardens and woods far below them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001482": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001482",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001483": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001483",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy found herself riding easily between two of the biggest Monkeys, one of them the King himself. They had made a chair of their hands and were careful not to hurt her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001484": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001484",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001485": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001485",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why do you have to obey the charm of the Golden Cap?” she asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001486": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001486",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001487": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001487",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is a long story,” answered the King, with a winged laugh; “but as we have a long journey before us, I will pass the time by telling you about it, if you wish.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001488": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001488",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001489": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001489",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I shall be glad to hear it,” she replied.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001490": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001490",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001491": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001491",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Once,” began the leader, “we were a free people, living happily in the great forest, flying from tree to tree, eating nuts and fruit, and doing just as we pleased without calling anybody master. Perhaps some of us were rather too full of mischief at times, flying down to pull the tails of the animals that had no wings, chasing birds, and throwing nuts at the people who walked in the forest. But we were careless and happy and full of fun, and enjoyed every minute of the day. This was many years ago, long before Oz came out of the clouds to rule over this land.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001492": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001492",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001493": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001493",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“There lived here then, away at the North, a beautiful princess, who was also a powerful sorceress. All her magic was used to help the people, and she was never known to hurt anyone who was good. Her name was Gayelette, and she lived in a handsome palace built from great blocks of ruby. Everyone loved her, but her greatest sorrow was that she could find no one to love in return, since all the men were much too stupid and ugly to mate with one so beautiful and wise. At last, however, she found a boy who was handsome and manly and wise beyond his years. Gayelette made up her mind that when he grew to be a man she would make him her husband, so she took him to her ruby palace and used all her magic powers to make him as strong and good and lovely as any woman could wish. When he grew to manhood, Quelala, as he was called, was said to be the best and wisest man in all the land, while his manly beauty was so great that Gayelette loved him dearly, and hastened to make everything ready for the wedding.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001494": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001494",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001495": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001495",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My grandfather was at that time the King of the Winged Monkeys which lived in the forest near Gayelette’s palace, and the old fellow loved a joke better than a good dinner. One day, just before the wedding, my grandfather was flying out with his band when he saw Quelala walking beside the river. He was dressed in a rich costume of pink silk and purple velvet, and my grandfather thought he would see what he could do. At his word the band flew down and seized Quelala, carried him in their arms until they were over the middle of the river, and then dropped him into the water.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001496": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001496",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001497": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001497",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“‘Swim out, my fine fellow,’ cried my grandfather, ‘and see if the water has spotted your clothes.’ Quelala was much too wise not to swim, and he was not in the least spoiled by all his good fortune. He laughed, when he came to the top of the water, and swam in to shore. But when Gayelette came running out to him she found his silks and velvet all ruined by the river.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001498": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001498",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001499": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001499",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The princess was angry, and she knew, of course, who did it. She had all the Winged Monkeys brought before her, and she said at first that their wings should be tied and they should be treated as they had treated Quelala, and dropped in the river. But my grandfather pleaded hard, for he knew the Monkeys would drown in the river with their wings tied, and Quelala said a kind word for them also; so that Gayelette finally spared them, on condition that the Winged Monkeys should ever after do three times the bidding of the owner of the Golden Cap. This Cap had been made for a wedding present to Quelala, and it is said to have cost the princess half her kingdom. Of course my grandfather and all the other Monkeys at once agreed to the condition, and that is how it happens that we are three times the slaves of the owner of the Golden Cap, whosoever he may be.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001500": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001500",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001501": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001501",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And what became of them?” asked Dorothy, who had been greatly interested in the story.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001502": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001502",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001503": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001503",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Quelala being the first owner of the Golden Cap,” replied the Monkey, “he was the first to lay his wishes upon us. As his bride could not bear the sight of us, he called us all to him in the forest after he had married her and ordered us always to keep where she could never again set eyes on a Winged Monkey, which we were glad to do, for we were all afraid of her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001504": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001504",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001505": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001505",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This was all we ever had to do until the Golden Cap fell into the hands of the Wicked Witch of the West, who made us enslave the Winkies, and afterward drive Oz himself out of the Land of the West. Now the Golden Cap is yours, and three times you have the right to lay your wishes upon us.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001506": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001506",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001507": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001507",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>As the Monkey King finished his story Dorothy looked down and saw the green, shining walls of the Emerald City before them. She wondered at the rapid flight of the Monkeys, but was glad the journey was over. The strange creatures set the travelers down carefully before the gate of the City, the King bowed low to Dorothy, and then flew swiftly away, followed by all his band.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001508": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001508",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001509": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001509",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That was a good ride,” said the little girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001510": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001510",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001511": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001511",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yes, and a quick way out of our troubles,” replied the Lion. “How lucky it was you brought away that wonderful Cap!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001512": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001512",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001513": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001513",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001514": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001514",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XV<br>\nThe Discovery of Oz, the Terrible</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001515": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001515",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001516": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001516",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The four travelers walked up to the great gate of Emerald City and rang the bell. After ringing several times, it was opened by the same Guardian of the Gates they had met before.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001517": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001517",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001518": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001518",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What! are you back again?” he asked, in surprise.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001519": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001519",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001520": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001520",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Do you not see us?” answered the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001521": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001521",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001522": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001522",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But I thought you had gone to visit the Wicked Witch of the West.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001523": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001523",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001524": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001524",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We did visit her,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001525": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001525",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001526": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001526",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And she let you go again?” asked the man, in wonder.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001527": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001527",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001528": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001528",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“She could not help it, for she is melted,” explained the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001529": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001529",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001530": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001530",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Melted! Well, that is good news, indeed,” said the man. “Who melted her?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001531": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001531",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001532": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001532",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It was Dorothy,” said the Lion gravely.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001533": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001533",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001534": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001534",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Good gracious!” exclaimed the man, and he bowed very low indeed before her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001535": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001535",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001536": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001536",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then he led them into his little room and locked the spectacles from the great box on all their eyes, just as he had done before. Afterward they passed on through the gate into the Emerald City. When the people heard from the Guardian of the Gates that Dorothy had melted the Wicked Witch of the West, they all gathered around the travelers and followed them in a great crowd to the Palace of Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001537": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001537",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001538": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001538",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The soldier with the green whiskers was still on guard before the door, but he let them in at once, and they were again met by the beautiful green girl, who showed each of them to their old rooms at once, so they might rest until the Great Oz was ready to receive them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001539": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001539",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001540": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001540",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The soldier had the news carried straight to Oz that Dorothy and the other travelers had come back again, after destroying the Wicked Witch; but Oz made no reply. They thought the Great Wizard would send for them at once, but he did not. They had no word from him the next day, nor the next, nor the next. The waiting was tiresome and wearing, and at last they grew vexed that Oz should treat them in so poor a fashion, after sending them to undergo hardships and slavery. So the Scarecrow at last asked the green girl to take another message to Oz, saying if he did not let them in to see him at once they would call the Winged Monkeys to help them, and find out whether he kept his promises or not. When the Wizard was given this message he was so frightened that he sent word for them to come to the Throne Room at four minutes after nine o’clock the next morning. He had once met the Winged Monkeys in the Land of the West, and he did not wish to meet them again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001541": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001541",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001542": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001542",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The four travelers passed a sleepless night, each thinking of the gift Oz had promised to bestow on him. Dorothy fell asleep only once, and then she dreamed she was in Kansas, where Aunt Em was telling her how glad she was to have her little girl at home again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001543": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001543",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001544": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001544",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Promptly at nine o’clock the next morning the green-whiskered soldier came to them, and four minutes later they all went into the Throne Room of the Great Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001545": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001545",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001546": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001546",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Of course each one of them expected to see the Wizard in the shape he had taken before, and all were greatly surprised when they looked about and saw no one at all in the room. They kept close to the door and closer to one another, for the stillness of the empty room was more dreadful than any of the forms they had seen Oz take.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001547": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001547",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Presently they heard a solemn Voice, that seemed to come from somewhere near the top of the great dome, and it said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001549": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001549",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001550": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001550",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am Oz, the Great and Terrible. Why do you seek me?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001551": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001551",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001552": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001552",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They looked again in every part of the room, and then, seeing no one, Dorothy asked, “Where are you?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001553": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001553",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001554": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001554",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am everywhere,” answered the Voice, “but to the eyes of common mortals I am invisible. I will now seat myself upon my throne, that you may converse with me.” Indeed, the Voice seemed just then to come straight from the throne itself; so they walked toward it and stood in a row while Dorothy said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001555": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001555",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001556": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001556",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We have come to claim our promise, O Oz.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001557": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001557",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001558": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001558",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What promise?” asked Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001559": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001559",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001560": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001560",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You promised to send me back to Kansas when the Wicked Witch was destroyed,” said the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001561": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001561",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001562": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001562",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And you promised to give me brains,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001563": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001563",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001564": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001564",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And you promised to give me a heart,” said the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001565": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001565",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001566": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001566",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And you promised to give me courage,” said the Cowardly Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001567": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001567",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001568": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001568",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Is the Wicked Witch really destroyed?” asked the Voice, and Dorothy thought it trembled a little.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001569": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001569",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001570": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001570",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yes,” she answered, “I melted her with a bucket of water.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001571": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001571",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001572": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001572",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Dear me,” said the Voice, “how sudden! Well, come to me tomorrow, for I must have time to think it over.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001573": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001573",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001574": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001574",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You’ve had plenty of time already,” said the Tin Woodman angrily.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001575": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001575",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001576": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001576",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We shan’t wait a day longer,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001577": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001577",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001578": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001578",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You must keep your promises to us!” exclaimed Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001579": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001579",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001580": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001580",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion thought it might be as well to frighten the Wizard, so he gave a large, loud roar, which was so fierce and dreadful that Toto jumped away from him in alarm and tipped over the screen that stood in a corner. As it fell with a crash they looked that way, and the next moment all of them were filled with wonder. For they saw, standing in just the spot the screen had hidden, a little old man, with a bald head and a wrinkled face, who seemed to be as much surprised as they were. The Tin Woodman, raising his axe, rushed toward the little man and cried out, “Who are you?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001581": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001581",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001582": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001582",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am Oz, the Great and Terrible,” said the little man, in a trembling voice. “But don’t strike me—please don’t—and I’ll do anything you want me to.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001583": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001583",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001584": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001584",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Our friends looked at him in surprise and dismay.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001585": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001585",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001586": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001586",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I thought Oz was a great Head,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001587": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001587",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001588": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001588",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I thought Oz was a lovely Lady,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001589": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001589",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001590": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001590",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I thought Oz was a terrible Beast,” said the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001591": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001591",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001592": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001592",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I thought Oz was a Ball of Fire,” exclaimed the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001593": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001593",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001594": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001594",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No, you are all wrong,” said the little man meekly. “I have been making believe.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001595": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001595",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001596": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001596",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Making believe!” cried Dorothy. “Are you not a Great Wizard?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001597": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001597",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001598": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001598",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Hush, my dear,” he said. “Don’t speak so loud, or you will be overheard—and I should be ruined. I’m supposed to be a Great Wizard.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001599": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001599",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001600": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001600",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And aren’t you?” she asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001601": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001601",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001602": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001602",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Not a bit of it, my dear; I’m just a common man.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001603": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001603",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001604": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001604",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You’re more than that,” said the Scarecrow, in a grieved tone; “you’re a humbug.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001605": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001605",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001606": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001606",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Exactly so!” declared the little man, rubbing his hands together as if it pleased him. “I am a humbug.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001607": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001607",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001608": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001608",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But this is terrible,” said the Tin Woodman. “How shall I ever get my heart?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001609": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001609",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001610": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001610",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Or I my courage?” asked the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001611": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001611",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001612": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001612",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Or I my brains?” wailed the Scarecrow, wiping the tears from his eyes with his coat sleeve.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001613": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001613",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001614": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001614",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My dear friends,” said Oz, “I pray you not to speak of these little things. Think of me, and the terrible trouble I’m in at being found out.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001615": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001615",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001616": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001616",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Doesn’t anyone else know you’re a humbug?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001617": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001617",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001618": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001618",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No one knows it but you four—and myself,” replied Oz. “I have fooled everyone so long that I thought I should never be found out. It was a great mistake my ever letting you into the Throne Room. Usually I will not see even my subjects, and so they believe I am something terrible.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001619": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001619",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001620": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001620",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But, I don’t understand,” said Dorothy, in bewilderment. “How was it that you appeared to me as a great Head?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001621": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001621",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001622": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001622",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That was one of my tricks,” answered Oz. “Step this way, please, and I will tell you all about it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001623": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001623",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001624": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001624",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>He led the way to a small chamber in the rear of the Throne Room, and they all followed him. He pointed to one corner, in which lay the great Head, made out of many thicknesses of paper, and with a carefully painted face.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001625": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001625",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001626": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001626",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This I hung from the ceiling by a wire,” said Oz. “I stood behind the screen and pulled a thread, to make the eyes move and the mouth open.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001627": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001627",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001628": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001628",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But how about the voice?” she inquired.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001629": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001629",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001630": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001630",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, I am a ventriloquist,” said the little man. “I can throw the sound of my voice wherever I wish, so that you thought it was coming out of the Head. Here are the other things I used to deceive you.” He showed the Scarecrow the dress and the mask he had worn when he seemed to be the lovely Lady. And the Tin Woodman saw that his terrible Beast was nothing but a lot of skins, sewn together, with slats to keep their sides out. As for the Ball of Fire, the false Wizard had hung that also from the ceiling. It was really a ball of cotton, but when oil was poured upon it the ball burned fiercely.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001631": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001631",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001632": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001632",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Really,” said the Scarecrow, “you ought to be ashamed of yourself for being such a humbug.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001633": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001633",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001634": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001634",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am—I certainly am,” answered the little man sorrowfully; “but it was the only thing I could do. Sit down, please, there are plenty of chairs; and I will tell you my story.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001635": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001635",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001636": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001636",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So they sat down and listened while he told the following tale.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001637": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001637",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001638": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001638",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I was born in Omaha—”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001639": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001639",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001640": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001640",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why, that isn’t very far from Kansas!” cried Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001641": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001641",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001642": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001642",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No, but it’s farther from here,” he said, shaking his head at her sadly. “When I grew up I became a ventriloquist, and at that I was very well trained by a great master. I can imitate any kind of a bird or beast.” Here he mewed so like a kitten that Toto pricked up his ears and looked everywhere to see where she was. “After a time,” continued Oz, “I tired of that, and became a balloonist.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001643": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001643",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001644": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001644",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What is that?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001645": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001645",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001646": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001646",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“A man who goes up in a balloon on circus day, so as to draw a crowd of people together and get them to pay to see the circus,” he explained.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001647": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001647",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001648": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001648",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh,” she said, “I know.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001649": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001649",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001650": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001650",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well, one day I went up in a balloon and the ropes got twisted, so that I couldn’t come down again. It went way up above the clouds, so far that a current of air struck it and carried it many, many miles away. For a day and a night I traveled through the air, and on the morning of the second day I awoke and found the balloon floating over a strange and beautiful country.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001651": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001651",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001652": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001652",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It came down gradually, and I was not hurt a bit. But I found myself in the midst of a strange people, who, seeing me come from the clouds, thought I was a great Wizard. Of course I let them think so, because they were afraid of me, and promised to do anything I wished them to.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001653": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001653",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001654": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001654",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Just to amuse myself, and keep the good people busy, I ordered them to build this City, and my Palace; and they did it all willingly and well. Then I thought, as the country was so green and beautiful, I would call it the Emerald City; and to make the name fit better I put green spectacles on all the people, so that everything they saw was green.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001655": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001655",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001656": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001656",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But isn’t everything here green?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001657": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001657",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001658": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001658",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No more than in any other city,” replied Oz; “but when you wear green spectacles, why of course everything you see looks green to you. The Emerald City was built a great many years ago, for I was a young man when the balloon brought me here, and I am a very old man now. But my people have worn green glasses on their eyes so long that most of them think it really is an Emerald City, and it certainly is a beautiful place, abounding in jewels and precious metals, and every good thing that is needed to make one happy. I have been good to the people, and they like me; but ever since this Palace was built, I have shut myself up and would not see any of them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001659": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001659",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001660": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001660",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“One of my greatest fears was the Witches, for while I had no magical powers at all I soon found out that the Witches were really able to do wonderful things. There were four of them in this country, and they ruled the people who live in the North and South and East and West. Fortunately, the Witches of the North and South were good, and I knew they would do me no harm; but the Witches of the East and West were terribly wicked, and had they not thought I was more powerful than they themselves, they would surely have destroyed me. As it was, I lived in deadly fear of them for many years; so you can imagine how pleased I was when I heard your house had fallen on the Wicked Witch of the East. When you came to me, I was willing to promise anything if you would only do away with the other Witch; but, now that you have melted her, I am ashamed to say that I cannot keep my promises.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001661": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001661",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001662": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001662",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I think you are a very bad man,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001663": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001663",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001664": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001664",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, no, my dear; I’m really a very good man, but I’m a very bad Wizard, I must admit.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001665": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001665",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001666": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001666",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Can’t you give me brains?” asked the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001667": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001667",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001668": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001668",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You don’t need them. You are learning something every day. A baby has brains, but it doesn’t know much. Experience is the only thing that brings knowledge, and the longer you are on earth the more experience you are sure to get.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001669": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001669",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001670": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001670",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That may all be true,” said the Scarecrow, “but I shall be very unhappy unless you give me brains.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001671": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001671",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001672": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001672",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The false Wizard looked at him carefully.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001673": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001673",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001674": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001674",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well,” he said with a sigh, “I’m not much of a magician, as I said; but if you will come to me tomorrow morning, I will stuff your head with brains. I cannot tell you how to use them, however; you must find that out for yourself.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001675": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001675",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001676": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001676",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, thank you—thank you!” cried the Scarecrow. “I’ll find a way to use them, never fear!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001677": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001677",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001678": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001678",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But how about my courage?” asked the Lion anxiously.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001679": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001679",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001680": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001680",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You have plenty of courage, I am sure,” answered Oz. “All you need is confidence in yourself. There is no living thing that is not afraid when it faces danger. The True courage is in facing danger when you are afraid, and that kind of courage you have in plenty.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001681": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001681",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001682": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001682",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Perhaps I have, but I’m scared just the same,” said the Lion. “I shall really be very unhappy unless you give me the sort of courage that makes one forget he is afraid.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001683": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001683",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001684": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001684",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Very well, I will give you that sort of courage tomorrow,” replied Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001685": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001685",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001686": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001686",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How about my heart?” asked the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001687": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001687",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001688": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001688",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why, as for that,” answered Oz, “I think you are wrong to want a heart. It makes most people unhappy. If you only knew it, you are in luck not to have a heart.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001689": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001689",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001690": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001690",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That must be a matter of opinion,” said the Tin Woodman. “For my part, I will bear all the unhappiness without a murmur, if you will give me the heart.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001691": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001691",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001692": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001692",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Very well,” answered Oz meekly. “Come to me tomorrow and you shall have a heart. I have played Wizard for so many years that I may as well continue the part a little longer.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001693": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001693",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001694": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001694",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And now,” said Dorothy, “how am I to get back to Kansas?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001695": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001695",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001696": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001696",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We shall have to think about that,” replied the little man. “Give me two or three days to consider the matter and I’ll try to find a way to carry you over the desert. In the meantime you shall all be treated as my guests, and while you live in the Palace my people will wait upon you and obey your slightest wish. There is only one thing I ask in return for my help—such as it is. You must keep my secret and tell no one I am a humbug.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001697": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001697",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001698": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001698",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They agreed to say nothing of what they had learned, and went back to their rooms in high spirits. Even Dorothy had hope that “The Great and Terrible Humbug,” as she called him, would find a way to send her back to Kansas, and if he did she was willing to forgive him everything.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001699": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001699",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001700": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001700",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001701": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001701",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XVI<br>\nThe Magic Art of the Great Humbug</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001702": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001702",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001703": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001703",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Next morning the Scarecrow said to his friends:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001704": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001704",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001705": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001705",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Congratulate me. I am going to Oz to get my brains at last. When I return I shall be as other men are.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001706": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001706",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001707": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001707",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I have always liked you as you were,” said Dorothy simply.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001708": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001708",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001709": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001709",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It is kind of you to like a Scarecrow,” he replied. “But surely you will think more of me when you hear the splendid thoughts my new brain is going to turn out.” Then he said good-bye to them all in a cheerful voice and went to the Throne Room, where he rapped upon the door.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001710": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001710",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001711": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001711",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come in,” said Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001712": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001712",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001713": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001713",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow went in and found the little man sitting down by the window, engaged in deep thought.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001714": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001714",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001715": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001715",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I have come for my brains,” remarked the Scarecrow, a little uneasily.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001716": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001716",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001717": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001717",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, yes; sit down in that chair, please,” replied Oz. “You must excuse me for taking your head off, but I shall have to do it in order to put your brains in their proper place.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001718": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001718",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001719": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001719",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That’s all right,” said the Scarecrow. “You are quite welcome to take my head off, as long as it will be a better one when you put it on again.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001720": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001720",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001721": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001721",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Wizard unfastened his head and emptied out the straw. Then he entered the back room and took up a measure of bran, which he mixed with a great many pins and needles. Having shaken them together thoroughly, he filled the top of the Scarecrow’s head with the mixture and stuffed the rest of the space with straw, to hold it in place.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001722": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001722",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001723": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001723",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When he had fastened the Scarecrow’s head on his body again he said to him, “Hereafter you will be a great man, for I have given you a lot of bran-new brains.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001724": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001724",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001725": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001725",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow was both pleased and proud at the fulfillment of his greatest wish, and having thanked Oz warmly he went back to his friends.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001726": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001726",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001727": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001727",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy looked at him curiously. His head was quite bulged out at the top with brains.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001728": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001728",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001729": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001729",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How do you feel?” she asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001730": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001730",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001731": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001731",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I feel wise indeed,” he answered earnestly. “When I get used to my brains I shall know everything.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001732": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001732",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001733": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001733",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why are those needles and pins sticking out of your head?” asked the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001734": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001734",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001735": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001735",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is proof that he is sharp,” remarked the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001736": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001736",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001737": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001737",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well, I must go to Oz and get my heart,” said the Woodman. So he walked to the Throne Room and knocked at the door.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001738": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001738",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001739": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001739",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come in,” called Oz, and the Woodman entered and said, “I have come for my heart.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001740": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001740",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001741": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001741",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Very well,” answered the little man. “But I shall have to cut a hole in your breast, so I can put your heart in the right place. I hope it won’t hurt you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001742": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001742",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001743": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001743",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, no,” answered the Woodman. “I shall not feel it at all.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001744": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001744",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001745": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001745",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So Oz brought a pair of tinsmith’s shears and cut a small, square hole in the left side of the Tin Woodman’s breast. Then, going to a chest of drawers, he took out a pretty heart, made entirely of silk and stuffed with sawdust.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001746": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001746",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001747": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001747",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Isn’t it a beauty?” he asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001748": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001748",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001749": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001749",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It is, indeed!” replied the Woodman, who was greatly pleased. “But is it a kind heart?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001750": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001750",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001751": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001751",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, very!” answered Oz. He put the heart in the Woodman’s breast and then replaced the square of tin, soldering it neatly together where it had been cut.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001752": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001752",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001753": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001753",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“There,” said he; “now you have a heart that any man might be proud of. I’m sorry I had to put a patch on your breast, but it really couldn’t be helped.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001754": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001754",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001755": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001755",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Never mind the patch,” exclaimed the happy Woodman. “I am very grateful to you, and shall never forget your kindness.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001756": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001756",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001757": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001757",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Don’t speak of it,” replied Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001758": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001758",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001759": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001759",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then the Tin Woodman went back to his friends, who wished him every joy on account of his good fortune.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion now walked to the Throne Room and knocked at the door.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come in,” said Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I have come for my courage,” announced the Lion, entering the room.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001766": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001766",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001767": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001767",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Very well,” answered the little man; “I will get it for you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001768": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001768",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001769": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001769",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>He went to a cupboard and reaching up to a high shelf took down a square green bottle, the contents of which he poured into a green-gold dish, beautifully carved. Placing this before the Cowardly Lion, who sniffed at it as if he did not like it, the Wizard said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001770": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001770",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001771": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001771",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Drink.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001772": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001772",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001773": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001773",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What is it?” asked the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001774": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001774",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001775": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001775",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well,” answered Oz, “if it were inside of you, it would be courage. You know, of course, that courage is always inside one; so that this really cannot be called courage until you have swallowed it. Therefore I advise you to drink it as soon as possible.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001776": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001776",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001777": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001777",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion hesitated no longer, but drank till the dish was empty.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001778": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001778",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001779": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001779",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How do you feel now?” asked Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001780": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001780",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001781": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001781",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Full of courage,” replied the Lion, who went joyfully back to his friends to tell them of his good fortune.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001782": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001782",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001783": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001783",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Oz, left to himself, smiled to think of his success in giving the Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman and the Lion exactly what they thought they wanted. “How can I help being a humbug,” he said, “when all these people make me do things that everybody knows can’t be done? It was easy to make the Scarecrow and the Lion and the Woodman happy, because they imagined I could do anything. But it will take more than imagination to carry Dorothy back to Kansas, and I’m sure I don’t know how it can be done.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001784": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001784",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001785": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001785",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001786": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001786",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XVII<br>\nHow the Balloon Was Launched</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001787": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001787",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001788": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001788",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>For three days Dorothy heard nothing from Oz. These were sad days for the little girl, although her friends were all quite happy and contented. The Scarecrow told them there were wonderful thoughts in his head; but he would not say what they were because he knew no one could understand them but himself. When the Tin Woodman walked about he felt his heart rattling around in his breast; and he told Dorothy he had discovered it to be a kinder and more tender heart than the one he had owned when he was made of flesh. The Lion declared he was afraid of nothing on earth, and would gladly face an army or a dozen of the fierce Kalidahs.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001789": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001789",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001790": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001790",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Thus each of the little party was satisfied except Dorothy, who longed more than ever to get back to Kansas.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001791": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001791",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001792": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001792",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>On the fourth day, to her great joy, Oz sent for her, and when she entered the Throne Room he greeted her pleasantly:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001793": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001793",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001794": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001794",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Sit down, my dear; I think I have found the way to get you out of this country.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001795": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001795",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001796": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001796",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And back to Kansas?” she asked eagerly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001797": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001797",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001798": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001798",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well, I’m not sure about Kansas,” said Oz, “for I haven’t the faintest notion which way it lies. But the first thing to do is to cross the desert, and then it should be easy to find your way home.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001799": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001799",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001800": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001800",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How can I cross the desert?” she inquired.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001801": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001801",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001802": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001802",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well, I’ll tell you what I think,” said the little man. “You see, when I came to this country it was in a balloon. You also came through the air, being carried by a cyclone. So I believe the best way to get across the desert will be through the air. Now, it is quite beyond my powers to make a cyclone; but I’ve been thinking the matter over, and I believe I can make a balloon.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001803": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001803",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001804": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001804",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001805": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001805",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001806": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001806",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“A balloon,” said Oz, “is made of silk, which is coated with glue to keep the gas in it. I have plenty of silk in the Palace, so it will be no trouble to make the balloon. But in all this country there is no gas to fill the balloon with, to make it float.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001807": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001807",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001808": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001808",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If it won’t float,” remarked Dorothy, “it will be of no use to us.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001809": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001809",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001810": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001810",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“True,” answered Oz. “But there is another way to make it float, which is to fill it with hot air. Hot air isn’t as good as gas, for if the air should get cold the balloon would come down in the desert, and we should be lost.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001811": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001811",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001812": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001812",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We!” exclaimed the girl. “Are you going with me?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001813": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001813",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001814": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001814",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yes, of course,” replied Oz. “I am tired of being such a humbug. If I should go out of this Palace my people would soon discover I am not a Wizard, and then they would be vexed with me for having deceived them. So I have to stay shut up in these rooms all day, and it gets tiresome. I’d much rather go back to Kansas with you and be in a circus again.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001815": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001815",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001816": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001816",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I shall be glad to have your company,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001817": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001817",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001818": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001818",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Thank you,” he answered. “Now, if you will help me sew the silk together, we will begin to work on our balloon.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001819": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001819",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001820": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001820",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So Dorothy took a needle and thread, and as fast as Oz cut the strips of silk into proper shape the girl sewed them neatly together. First there was a strip of light green silk, then a strip of dark green and then a strip of emerald green; for Oz had a fancy to make the balloon in different shades of the color about them. It took three days to sew all the strips together, but when it was finished they had a big bag of green silk more than twenty feet long.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001821": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001821",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001822": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001822",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then Oz painted it on the inside with a coat of thin glue, to make it airtight, after which he announced that the balloon was ready.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001823": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001823",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001824": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001824",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But we must have a basket to ride in,” he said. So he sent the soldier with the green whiskers for a big clothes basket, which he fastened with many ropes to the bottom of the balloon.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001825": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001825",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001826": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001826",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When it was all ready, Oz sent word to his people that he was going to make a visit to a great brother Wizard who lived in the clouds. The news spread rapidly throughout the city and everyone came to see the wonderful sight.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001827": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001827",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001828": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001828",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Oz ordered the balloon carried out in front of the Palace, and the people gazed upon it with much curiosity. The Tin Woodman had chopped a big pile of wood, and now he made a fire of it, and Oz held the bottom of the balloon over the fire so that the hot air that arose from it would be caught in the silken bag. Gradually the balloon swelled out and rose into the air, until finally the basket just touched the ground.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001829": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001829",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001830": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001830",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then Oz got into the basket and said to all the people in a loud voice:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001831": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001831",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001832": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001832",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I am now going away to make a visit. While I am gone the Scarecrow will rule over you. I command you to obey him as you would me.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001833": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001833",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001834": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001834",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The balloon was by this time tugging hard at the rope that held it to the ground, for the air within it was hot, and this made it so much lighter in weight than the air without that it pulled hard to rise into the sky.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001835": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001835",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001836": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001836",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come, Dorothy!” cried the Wizard. “Hurry up, or the balloon will fly away.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001837": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001837",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001838": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001838",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I can’t find Toto anywhere,” replied Dorothy, who did not wish to leave her little dog behind. Toto had run into the crowd to bark at a kitten, and Dorothy at last found him. She picked him up and ran towards the balloon.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001839": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001839",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001840": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001840",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She was within a few steps of it, and Oz was holding out his hands to help her into the basket, when, crack! went the ropes, and the balloon rose into the air without her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001841": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001841",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001842": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001842",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come back!” she screamed. “I want to go, too!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001843": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001843",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001844": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001844",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I can’t come back, my dear,” called Oz from the basket. “Good-bye!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001845": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001845",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001846": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001846",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Good-bye!” shouted everyone, and all eyes were turned upward to where the Wizard was riding in the basket, rising every moment farther and farther into the sky.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001847": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001847",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001848": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001848",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>And that was the last any of them ever saw of Oz, the Wonderful Wizard, though he may have reached Omaha safely, and be there now, for all we know. But the people remembered him lovingly, and said to one another:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001849": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001849",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001850": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001850",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oz was always our friend. When he was here he built for us this beautiful Emerald City, and now he is gone he has left the Wise Scarecrow to rule over us.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001851": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001851",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001852": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001852",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Still, for many days they grieved over the loss of the Wonderful Wizard, and would not be comforted.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001853": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001853",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001854": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001854",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001855": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001855",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XVIII<br>\nAway to the South</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001856": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001856",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001857": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001857",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy wept bitterly at the passing of her hope to get home to Kansas again; but when she thought it all over she was glad she had not gone up in a balloon. And she also felt sorry at losing Oz, and so did her companions.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001858": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001858",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001859": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001859",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Tin Woodman came to her and said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001860": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001860",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001861": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001861",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Truly I should be ungrateful if I failed to mourn for the man who gave me my lovely heart. I should like to cry a little because Oz is gone, if you will kindly wipe away my tears, so that I shall not rust.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001862": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001862",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001863": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001863",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“With pleasure,” she answered, and brought a towel at once. Then the Tin Woodman wept for several minutes, and she watched the tears carefully and wiped them away with the towel. When he had finished, he thanked her kindly and oiled himself thoroughly with his jeweled oil-can, to guard against mishap.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001864": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001864",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001865": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001865",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow was now the ruler of the Emerald City, and although he was not a Wizard the people were proud of him. “For,” they said, “there is not another city in all the world that is ruled by a stuffed man.” And, so far as they knew, they were quite right.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001866": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001866",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001867": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001867",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The morning after the balloon had gone up with Oz, the four travelers met in the Throne Room and talked matters over. The Scarecrow sat in the big throne and the others stood respectfully before him.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001868": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001868",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001869": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001869",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We are not so unlucky,” said the new ruler, “for this Palace and the Emerald City belong to us, and we can do just as we please. When I remember that a short time ago I was up on a pole in a farmer’s cornfield, and that now I am the ruler of this beautiful City, I am quite satisfied with my lot.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001870": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001870",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001871": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001871",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I also,” said the Tin Woodman, “am well-pleased with my new heart; and, really, that was the only thing I wished in all the world.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001872": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001872",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001873": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001873",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“For my part, I am content in knowing I am as brave as any beast that ever lived, if not braver,” said the Lion modestly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001874": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001874",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001875": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001875",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If Dorothy would only be contented to live in the Emerald City,” continued the Scarecrow, “we might all be happy together.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001876": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001876",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001877": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001877",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But I don’t want to live here,” cried Dorothy. “I want to go to Kansas, and live with Aunt Em and Uncle Henry.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001878": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001878",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001879": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001879",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well, then, what can be done?” inquired the Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001880": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001880",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001881": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001881",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow decided to think, and he thought so hard that the pins and needles began to stick out of his brains. Finally he said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001882": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001882",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001883": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001883",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why not call the Winged Monkeys, and ask them to carry you over the desert?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001884": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001884",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001885": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001885",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I never thought of that!” said Dorothy joyfully. “It’s just the thing. I’ll go at once for the Golden Cap.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001886": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001886",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001887": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001887",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When she brought it into the Throne Room she spoke the magic words, and soon the band of Winged Monkeys flew in through the open window and stood beside her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001888": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001888",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001889": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001889",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This is the second time you have called us,” said the Monkey King, bowing before the little girl. “What do you wish?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001890": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001890",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001891": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001891",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I want you to fly with me to Kansas,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001892": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001892",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001893": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001893",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the Monkey King shook his head.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001894": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001894",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001895": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001895",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That cannot be done,” he said. “We belong to this country alone, and cannot leave it. There has never been a Winged Monkey in Kansas yet, and I suppose there never will be, for they don’t belong there. We shall be glad to serve you in any way in our power, but we cannot cross the desert. Good-bye.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001896": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001896",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001897": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001897",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>And with another bow, the Monkey King spread his wings and flew away through the window, followed by all his band.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001898": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001898",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001899": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001899",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy was ready to cry with disappointment. “I have wasted the charm of the Golden Cap to no purpose,” she said, “for the Winged Monkeys cannot help me.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001900": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001900",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001901": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001901",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It is certainly too bad!” said the tender-hearted Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001902": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001902",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001903": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001903",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow was thinking again, and his head bulged out so horribly that Dorothy feared it would burst.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001904": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001904",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001905": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001905",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Let us call in the soldier with the green whiskers,” he said, “and ask his advice.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001906": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001906",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001907": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001907",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the soldier was summoned and entered the Throne Room timidly, for while Oz was alive he never was allowed to come farther than the door.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001908": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001908",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001909": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001909",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This little girl,” said the Scarecrow to the soldier, “wishes to cross the desert. How can she do so?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001910": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001910",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001911": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001911",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I cannot tell,” answered the soldier, “for nobody has ever crossed the desert, unless it is Oz himself.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001912": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001912",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001913": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001913",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Is there no one who can help me?” asked Dorothy earnestly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001914": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001914",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001915": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001915",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Glinda might,” he suggested.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001916": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001916",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001917": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001917",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Who is Glinda?” inquired the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001918": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001918",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001919": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001919",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The Witch of the South. She is the most powerful of all the Witches, and rules over the Quadlings. Besides, her castle stands on the edge of the desert, so she may know a way to cross it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001920": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001920",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001921": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001921",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Glinda is a Good Witch, isn’t she?” asked the child.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001922": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001922",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001923": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001923",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The Quadlings think she is good,” said the soldier, “and she is kind to everyone. I have heard that Glinda is a beautiful woman, who knows how to keep young in spite of the many years she has lived.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001924": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001924",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001925": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001925",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How can I get to her castle?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001926": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001926",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001927": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001927",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The road is straight to the South,” he answered, “but it is said to be full of dangers to travelers. There are wild beasts in the woods, and a race of queer men who do not like strangers to cross their country. For this reason none of the Quadlings ever come to the Emerald City.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001928": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001928",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001929": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001929",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The soldier then left them and the Scarecrow said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001930": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001930",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001931": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001931",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It seems, in spite of dangers, that the best thing Dorothy can do is to travel to the Land of the South and ask Glinda to help her. For, of course, if Dorothy stays here she will never get back to Kansas.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001932": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001932",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001933": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001933",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You must have been thinking again,” remarked the Tin Woodman.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001934": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001934",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001935": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001935",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I have,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001936": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001936",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001937": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001937",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I shall go with Dorothy,” declared the Lion, “for I am tired of your city and long for the woods and the country again. I am really a wild beast, you know. Besides, Dorothy will need someone to protect her.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001938": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001938",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001939": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001939",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That is true,” agreed the Woodman. “My axe may be of service to her; so I also will go with her to the Land of the South.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001940": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001940",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001941": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001941",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“When shall we start?” asked the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001942": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001942",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001943": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001943",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Are you going?” they asked, in surprise.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001944": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001944",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001945": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001945",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Certainly. If it wasn’t for Dorothy I should never have had brains. She lifted me from the pole in the cornfield and brought me to the Emerald City. So my good luck is all due to her, and I shall never leave her until she starts back to Kansas for good and all.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001946": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001946",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001947": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001947",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Thank you,” said Dorothy gratefully. “You are all very kind to me. But I should like to start as soon as possible.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001948": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001948",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001949": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001949",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We shall go tomorrow morning,” returned the Scarecrow. “So now let us all get ready, for it will be a long journey.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001950": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001950",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001951": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001951",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001952": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001952",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XIX<br>\nAttacked by the Fighting Trees</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001953": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001953",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001954": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001954",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The next morning Dorothy kissed the pretty green girl good-bye, and they all shook hands with the soldier with the green whiskers, who had walked with them as far as the gate. When the Guardian of the Gate saw them again he wondered greatly that they could leave the beautiful City to get into new trouble. But he at once unlocked their spectacles, which he put back into the green box, and gave them many good wishes to carry with them.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001955": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001955",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001956": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001956",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You are now our ruler,” he said to the Scarecrow; “so you must come back to us as soon as possible.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001957": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001957",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001958": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001958",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I certainly shall if I am able,” the Scarecrow replied; “but I must help Dorothy to get home, first.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001959": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001959",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001960": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001960",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>As Dorothy bade the good-natured Guardian a last farewell she said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001961": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001961",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001962": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001962",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I have been very kindly treated in your lovely City, and everyone has been good to me. I cannot tell you how grateful I am.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001963": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001963",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001964": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001964",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Don’t try, my dear,” he answered. “We should like to keep you with us, but if it is your wish to return to Kansas, I hope you will find a way.” He then opened the gate of the outer wall, and they walked forth and started upon their journey.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001965": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001965",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001966": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001966",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The sun shone brightly as our friends turned their faces toward the Land of the South. They were all in the best of spirits, and laughed and chatted together. Dorothy was once more filled with the hope of getting home, and the Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman were glad to be of use to her. As for the Lion, he sniffed the fresh air with delight and whisked his tail from side to side in pure joy at being in the country again, while Toto ran around them and chased the moths and butterflies, barking merrily all the time.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001967": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001967",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001968": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001968",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“City life does not agree with me at all,” remarked the Lion, as they walked along at a brisk pace. “I have lost much flesh since I lived there, and now I am anxious for a chance to show the other beasts how courageous I have grown.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001969": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001969",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001970": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001970",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They now turned and took a last look at the Emerald City. All they could see was a mass of towers and steeples behind the green walls, and high up above everything the spires and dome of the Palace of Oz.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001971": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001971",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001972": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001972",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oz was not such a bad Wizard, after all,” said the Tin Woodman, as he felt his heart rattling around in his breast.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001973": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001973",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001974": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001974",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“He knew how to give me brains, and very good brains, too,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001975": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001975",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001976": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001976",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If Oz had taken a dose of the same courage he gave me,” added the Lion, “he would have been a brave man.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001977": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001977",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001978": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001978",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy said nothing. Oz had not kept the promise he made her, but he had done his best, so she forgave him. As he said, he was a good man, even if he was a bad Wizard.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001979": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001979",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001980": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001980",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The first day’s journey was through the green fields and bright flowers that stretched about the Emerald City on every side. They slept that night on the grass, with nothing but the stars over them; and they rested very well indeed.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001981": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001981",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001982": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001982",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>In the morning they traveled on until they came to a thick wood. There was no way of going around it, for it seemed to extend to the right and left as far as they could see; and, besides, they did not dare change the direction of their journey for fear of getting lost. So they looked for the place where it would be easiest to get into the forest.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001983": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001983",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001984": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001984",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow, who was in the lead, finally discovered a big tree with such wide-spreading branches that there was room for the party to pass underneath. So he walked forward to the tree, but just as he came under the first branches they bent down and twined around him, and the next minute he was raised from the ground and flung headlong among his fellow travelers.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001985": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001985",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001986": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001986",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>This did not hurt the Scarecrow, but it surprised him, and he looked rather dizzy when Dorothy picked him up.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001987": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001987",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001988": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001988",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Here is another space between the trees,” called the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001989": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001989",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001990": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001990",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Let me try it first,” said the Scarecrow, “for it doesn’t hurt me to get thrown about.” He walked up to another tree, as he spoke, but its branches immediately seized him and tossed him back again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001991": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001991",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001992": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001992",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This is strange,” exclaimed Dorothy. “What shall we do?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001993": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001993",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001994": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001994",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The trees seem to have made up their minds to fight us, and stop our journey,” remarked the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001995": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001995",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001996": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001996",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I believe I will try it myself,” said the Woodman, and shouldering his axe, he marched up to the first tree that had handled the Scarecrow so roughly. When a big branch bent down to seize him the Woodman chopped at it so fiercely that he cut it in two. At once the tree began shaking all its branches as if in pain, and the Tin Woodman passed safely under it.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001997": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001997",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001998": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001998",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Come on!” he shouted to the others. “Be quick!” They all ran forward and passed under the tree without injury, except Toto, who was caught by a small branch and shaken until he howled. But the Woodman promptly chopped off the branch and set the little dog free.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001999": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000001999",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002000": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002000",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The other trees of the forest did nothing to keep them back, so they made up their minds that only the first row of trees could bend down their branches, and that probably these were the policemen of the forest, and given this wonderful power in order to keep strangers out of it.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002001": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002001",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002002": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002002",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The four travelers walked with ease through the trees until they came to the farther edge of the wood. Then, to their surprise, they found before them a high wall which seemed to be made of white china. It was smooth, like the surface of a dish, and higher than their heads.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002003": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002003",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002004": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002004",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What shall we do now?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002005": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002005",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002006": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002006",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I will make a ladder,” said the Tin Woodman, “for we certainly must climb over the wall.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002007": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002007",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002008": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002008",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002009": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002009",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XX<br>\nThe Dainty China Country</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002010": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002010",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002011": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002011",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>While the Woodman was making a ladder from wood which he found in the forest Dorothy lay down and slept, for she was tired by the long walk. The Lion also curled himself up to sleep and Toto lay beside him.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002012": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002012",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002013": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002013",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow watched the Woodman while he worked, and said to him:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I cannot think why this wall is here, nor what it is made of.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Rest your brains and do not worry about the wall,” replied the Woodman. “When we have climbed over it, we shall know what is on the other side.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>After a time the ladder was finished. It looked clumsy, but the Tin Woodman was sure it was strong and would answer their purpose. The Scarecrow waked Dorothy and the Lion and Toto, and told them that the ladder was ready. The Scarecrow climbed up the ladder first, but he was so awkward that Dorothy had to follow close behind and keep him from falling off. When he got his head over the top of the wall the Scarecrow said, “Oh, my!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Go on,” exclaimed Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So the Scarecrow climbed farther up and sat down on the top of the wall, and Dorothy put her head over and cried, “Oh, my!” just as the Scarecrow had done.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then Toto came up, and immediately began to bark, but Dorothy made him be still.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion climbed the ladder next, and the Tin Woodman came last; but both of them cried, “Oh, my!” as soon as they looked over the wall. When they were all sitting in a row on the top of the wall, they looked down and saw a strange sight.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Before them was a great stretch of country having a floor as smooth and shining and white as the bottom of a big platter. Scattered around were many houses made entirely of china and painted in the brightest colors. These houses were quite small, the biggest of them reaching only as high as Dorothy’s waist. There were also pretty little barns, with china fences around them; and many cows and sheep and horses and pigs and chickens, all made of china, were standing about in groups.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the strangest of all were the people who lived in this queer country. There were milkmaids and shepherdesses, with brightly colored bodices and golden spots all over their gowns; and princesses with most gorgeous frocks of silver and gold and purple; and shepherds dressed in knee breeches with pink and yellow and blue stripes down them, and golden buckles on their shoes; and princes with jeweled crowns upon their heads, wearing ermine robes and satin doublets; and funny clowns in ruffled gowns, with round red spots upon their cheeks and tall, pointed caps. And, strangest of all, these people were all made of china, even to their clothes, and were so small that the tallest of them was no higher than Dorothy’s knee.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>No one did so much as look at the travelers at first, except one little purple china dog with an extra-large head, which came to the wall and barked at them in a tiny voice, afterwards running away again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How shall we get down?” asked Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They found the ladder so heavy they could not pull it up, so the Scarecrow fell off the wall and the others jumped down upon him so that the hard floor would not hurt their feet. Of course they took pains not to light on his head and get the pins in their feet. When all were safely down they picked up the Scarecrow, whose body was quite flattened out, and patted his straw into shape again.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We must cross this strange place in order to get to the other side,” said Dorothy, “for it would be unwise for us to go any other way except due South.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They began walking through the country of the china people, and the first thing they came to was a china milkmaid milking a china cow. As they drew near, the cow suddenly gave a kick and kicked over the stool, the pail, and even the milkmaid herself, and all fell on the china ground with a great clatter.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002043": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002043",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy was shocked to see that the cow had broken her leg off, and that the pail was lying in several small pieces, while the poor milkmaid had a nick in her left elbow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002044": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002044",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002045": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002045",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“There!” cried the milkmaid angrily. “See what you have done! My cow has broken her leg, and I must take her to the mender’s shop and have it glued on again. What do you mean by coming here and frightening my cow?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002046": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002046",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002047": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002047",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I’m very sorry,” returned Dorothy. “Please forgive us.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002048": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002048",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002049": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002049",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>But the pretty milkmaid was much too vexed to make any answer. She picked up the leg sulkily and led her cow away, the poor animal limping on three legs. As she left them the milkmaid cast many reproachful glances over her shoulder at the clumsy strangers, holding her nicked elbow close to her side.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002050": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002050",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002051": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002051",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy was quite grieved at this mishap.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002052": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002052",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002053": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002053",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We must be very careful here,” said the kind-hearted Woodman, “or we may hurt these pretty little people so they will never get over it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002054": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002054",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002055": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002055",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>A little farther on Dorothy met a most beautifully dressed young Princess, who stopped short as she saw the strangers and started to run away.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002056": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002056",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002057": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002057",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy wanted to see more of the Princess, so she ran after her. But the china girl cried out:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002058": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002058",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002059": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002059",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Don’t chase me! Don’t chase me!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002060": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002060",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002061": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002061",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She had such a frightened little voice that Dorothy stopped and said, “Why not?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002062": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002062",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002063": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002063",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Because,” answered the Princess, also stopping, a safe distance away, “if I run I may fall down and break myself.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002064": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002064",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002065": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002065",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But could you not be mended?” asked the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002066": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002066",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002067": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002067",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, yes; but one is never so pretty after being mended, you know,” replied the Princess.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002068": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002068",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002069": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002069",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I suppose not,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002070": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002070",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002071": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002071",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Now there is Mr. Joker, one of our clowns,” continued the china lady, “who is always trying to stand upon his head. He has broken himself so often that he is mended in a hundred places, and doesn’t look at all pretty. Here he comes now, so you can see for yourself.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002072": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002072",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002073": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002073",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Indeed, a jolly little clown came walking toward them, and Dorothy could see that in spite of his pretty clothes of red and yellow and green he was completely covered with cracks, running every which way and showing plainly that he had been mended in many places.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002074": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002074",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002075": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002075",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Clown put his hands in his pockets, and after puffing out his cheeks and nodding his head at them saucily, he said:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002076": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002076",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002077": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002077",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p class=\"poem\">    “My lady fair,<br>\n   Why do you stare<br>\nAt poor old Mr. Joker?<br>\n    You’re quite as stiff<br>\n    And prim as if<br>\nYou’d eaten up a poker!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002078": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002078",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002079": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002079",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Be quiet, sir!” said the Princess. “Can’t you see these are strangers, and should be treated with respect?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002080": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002080",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002081": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002081",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Well, that’s respect, I expect,” declared the Clown, and immediately stood upon his head.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002082": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002082",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002083": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002083",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Don’t mind Mr. Joker,” said the Princess to Dorothy. “He is considerably cracked in his head, and that makes him foolish.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002084": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002084",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002085": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002085",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Oh, I don’t mind him a bit,” said Dorothy. “But you are so beautiful,” she continued, “that I am sure I could love you dearly. Won’t you let me carry you back to Kansas, and stand you on Aunt Em’s mantel? I could carry you in my basket.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002086": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002086",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002087": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002087",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That would make me very unhappy,” answered the china Princess. “You see, here in our country we live contentedly, and can talk and move around as we please. But whenever any of us are taken away our joints at once stiffen, and we can only stand straight and look pretty. Of course that is all that is expected of us when we are on mantels and cabinets and drawing-room tables, but our lives are much pleasanter here in our own country.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002088": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002088",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002089": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002089",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I would not make you unhappy for all the world!” exclaimed Dorothy. “So I’ll just say good-bye.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002090": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002090",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002091": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002091",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Good-bye,” replied the Princess.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002092": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002092",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002093": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002093",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They walked carefully through the china country. The little animals and all the people scampered out of their way, fearing the strangers would break them, and after an hour or so the travelers reached the other side of the country and came to another china wall.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002094": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002094",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002095": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002095",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>It was not so high as the first, however, and by standing upon the Lion’s back they all managed to scramble to the top. Then the Lion gathered his legs under him and jumped on the wall; but just as he jumped, he upset a china church with his tail and smashed it all to pieces.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002096": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002096",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002097": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002097",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That was too bad,” said Dorothy, “but really I think we were lucky in not doing these little people more harm than breaking a cow’s leg and a church. They are all so brittle!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002098": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002098",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002099": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002099",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“They are, indeed,” said the Scarecrow, “and I am thankful I am made of straw and cannot be easily damaged. There are worse things in the world than being a Scarecrow.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002100": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002100",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002101": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002101",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002102": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002102",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XXI<br>\nThe Lion Becomes the King of Beasts</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002103": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002103",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002104": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002104",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>After climbing down from the china wall the travelers found themselves in a disagreeable country, full of bogs and marshes and covered with tall, rank grass. It was difficult to walk without falling into muddy holes, for the grass was so thick that it hid them from sight. However, by carefully picking their way, they got safely along until they reached solid ground. But here the country seemed wilder than ever, and after a long and tiresome walk through the underbrush they entered another forest, where the trees were bigger and older than any they had ever seen.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002105": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002105",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002106": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002106",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This forest is perfectly delightful,” declared the Lion, looking around him with joy. “Never have I seen a more beautiful place.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002107": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002107",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002108": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002108",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It seems gloomy,” said the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002109": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002109",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002110": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002110",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Not a bit of it,” answered the Lion. “I should like to live here all my life. See how soft the dried leaves are under your feet and how rich and green the moss is that clings to these old trees. Surely no wild beast could wish a pleasanter home.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002111": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002111",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002112": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002112",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Perhaps there are wild beasts in the forest now,” said Dorothy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002113": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002113",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002114": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002114",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I suppose there are,” returned the Lion, “but I do not see any of them about.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002115": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002115",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002116": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002116",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>They walked through the forest until it became too dark to go any farther. Dorothy and Toto and the Lion lay down to sleep, while the Woodman and the Scarecrow kept watch over them as usual.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002117": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002117",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002118": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002118",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When morning came, they started again. Before they had gone far they heard a low rumble, as of the growling of many wild animals. Toto whimpered a little, but none of the others was frightened, and they kept along the well-trodden path until they came to an opening in the wood, in which were gathered hundreds of beasts of every variety. There were tigers and elephants and bears and wolves and foxes and all the others in the natural history, and for a moment Dorothy was afraid. But the Lion explained that the animals were holding a meeting, and he judged by their snarling and growling that they were in great trouble.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002119": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002119",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002120": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002120",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>As he spoke several of the beasts caught sight of him, and at once the great assemblage hushed as if by magic. The biggest of the tigers came up to the Lion and bowed, saying:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002121": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002121",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002122": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002122",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Welcome, O King of Beasts! You have come in good time to fight our enemy and bring peace to all the animals of the forest once more.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002123": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002123",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002124": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002124",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What is your trouble?” asked the Lion quietly.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002125": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002125",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002126": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002126",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We are all threatened,” answered the tiger, “by a fierce enemy which has lately come into this forest. It is a most tremendous monster, like a great spider, with a body as big as an elephant and legs as long as a tree trunk. It has eight of these long legs, and as the monster crawls through the forest he seizes an animal with a leg and drags it to his mouth, where he eats it as a spider does a fly. Not one of us is safe while this fierce creature is alive, and we had called a meeting to decide how to take care of ourselves when you came among us.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002127": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002127",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002128": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002128",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion thought for a moment.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002129": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002129",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002130": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002130",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Are there any other lions in this forest?” he asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002131": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002131",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002132": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002132",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“No; there were some, but the monster has eaten them all. And, besides, they were none of them nearly so large and brave as you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002133": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002133",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002134": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002134",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If I put an end to your enemy, will you bow down to me and obey me as King of the Forest?” inquired the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002135": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002135",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002136": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002136",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“We will do that gladly,” returned the tiger; and all the other beasts roared with a mighty roar: “We will!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002137": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002137",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002138": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002138",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Where is this great spider of yours now?” asked the Lion.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002139": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002139",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002140": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002140",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Yonder, among the oak trees,” said the tiger, pointing with his forefoot.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002141": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002141",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002142": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002142",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Take good care of these friends of mine,” said the Lion, “and I will go at once to fight the monster.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002143": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002143",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002144": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002144",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>He bade his comrades good-bye and marched proudly away to do battle with the enemy.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002145": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002145",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002146": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002146",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The great spider was lying asleep when the Lion found him, and it looked so ugly that its foe turned up his nose in disgust. Its legs were quite as long as the tiger had said, and its body covered with coarse black hair. It had a great mouth, with a row of sharp teeth a foot long; but its head was joined to the pudgy body by a neck as slender as a wasp’s waist. This gave the Lion a hint of the best way to attack the creature, and as he knew it was easier to fight it asleep than awake, he gave a great spring and landed directly upon the monster’s back. Then, with one blow of his heavy paw, all armed with sharp claws, he knocked the spider’s head from its body. Jumping down, he watched it until the long legs stopped wiggling, when he knew it was quite dead.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002147": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002147",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002148": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002148",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion went back to the opening where the beasts of the forest were waiting for him and said proudly:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002149": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002149",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002150": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002150",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You need fear your enemy no longer.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002151": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002151",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002152": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002152",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then the beasts bowed down to the Lion as their King, and he promised to come back and rule over them as soon as Dorothy was safely on her way to Kansas.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002153": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002153",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002154": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002154",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002155": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002155",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XXII<br>\nThe Country of the Quadlings</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002156": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002156",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002157": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002157",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The four travelers passed through the rest of the forest in safety, and when they came out from its gloom saw before them a steep hill, covered from top to bottom with great pieces of rock.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“That will be a hard climb,” said the Scarecrow, “but we must get over the hill, nevertheless.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>So he led the way and the others followed. They had nearly reached the first rock when they heard a rough voice cry out, “Keep back!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Who are you?” asked the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002165",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then a head showed itself over the rock and the same voice said, “This hill belongs to us, and we don’t allow anyone to cross it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002166": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002166",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002167": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002167",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But we must cross it,” said the Scarecrow. “We’re going to the country of the Quadlings.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002168": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002168",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002169": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002169",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But you shall not!” replied the voice, and there stepped from behind the rock the strangest man the travelers had ever seen.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002170": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002170",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002171": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002171",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>He was quite short and stout and had a big head, which was flat at the top and supported by a thick neck full of wrinkles. But he had no arms at all, and, seeing this, the Scarecrow did not fear that so helpless a creature could prevent them from climbing the hill. So he said, “I’m sorry not to do as you wish, but we must pass over your hill whether you like it or not,” and he walked boldly forward.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002172": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002172",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002173": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002173",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>As quick as lightning the man’s head shot forward and his neck stretched out until the top of the head, where it was flat, struck the Scarecrow in the middle and sent him tumbling, over and over, down the hill. Almost as quickly as it came the head went back to the body, and the man laughed harshly as he said, “It isn’t as easy as you think!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002174": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002174",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002175": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002175",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>A chorus of boisterous laughter came from the other rocks, and Dorothy saw hundreds of the armless Hammer-Heads upon the hillside, one behind every rock.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002176": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002176",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002177": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002177",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Lion became quite angry at the laughter caused by the Scarecrow’s mishap, and giving a loud roar that echoed like thunder, he dashed up the hill.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002178": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002178",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002179": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002179",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Again a head shot swiftly out, and the great Lion went rolling down the hill as if he had been struck by a cannon ball.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002180": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002180",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002181": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002181",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy ran down and helped the Scarecrow to his feet, and the Lion came up to her, feeling rather bruised and sore, and said, “It is useless to fight people with shooting heads; no one can withstand them.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002182": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002182",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002183": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002183",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What can we do, then?” she asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002184": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002184",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002185": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002185",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Call the Winged Monkeys,” suggested the Tin Woodman. “You have still the right to command them once more.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002186": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002186",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002187": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002187",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Very well,” she answered, and putting on the Golden Cap she uttered the magic words. The Monkeys were as prompt as ever, and in a few moments the entire band stood before her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002188": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002188",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002189": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002189",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What are your commands?” inquired the King of the Monkeys, bowing low.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002190": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002190",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002191": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002191",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Carry us over the hill to the country of the Quadlings,” answered the girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002192": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002192",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002193": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002193",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It shall be done,” said the King, and at once the Winged Monkeys caught the four travelers and Toto up in their arms and flew away with them. As they passed over the hill the Hammer-Heads yelled with vexation, and shot their heads high in the air, but they could not reach the Winged Monkeys, which carried Dorothy and her comrades safely over the hill and set them down in the beautiful country of the Quadlings.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002194": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002194",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002195": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002195",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This is the last time you can summon us,” said the leader to Dorothy; “so good-bye and good luck to you.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002196": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002196",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002197": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002197",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Good-bye, and thank you very much,” returned the girl; and the Monkeys rose into the air and were out of sight in a twinkling.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002198": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002198",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002199": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002199",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The country of the Quadlings seemed rich and happy. There was field upon field of ripening grain, with well-paved roads running between, and pretty rippling brooks with strong bridges across them. The fences and houses and bridges were all painted bright red, just as they had been painted yellow in the country of the Winkies and blue in the country of the Munchkins. The Quadlings themselves, who were short and fat and looked chubby and good-natured, were dressed all in red, which showed bright against the green grass and the yellowing grain.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002200": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002200",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002201": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002201",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Monkeys had set them down near a farmhouse, and the four travelers walked up to it and knocked at the door. It was opened by the farmer’s wife, and when Dorothy asked for something to eat the woman gave them all a good dinner, with three kinds of cake and four kinds of cookies, and a bowl of milk for Toto.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002202": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002202",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002203": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002203",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“How far is it to the Castle of Glinda?” asked the child.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002204": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002204",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002205": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002205",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“It is not a great way,” answered the farmer’s wife. “Take the road to the South and you will soon reach it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002206": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002206",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002207": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002207",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Thanking the good woman, they started afresh and walked by the fields and across the pretty bridges until they saw before them a very beautiful Castle. Before the gates were three young girls, dressed in handsome red uniforms trimmed with gold braid; and as Dorothy approached, one of them said to her:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002208": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002208",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002209": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002209",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Why have you come to the South Country?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002210": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002210",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002211": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002211",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“To see the Good Witch who rules here,” she answered. “Will you take me to her?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002212": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002212",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002213": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002213",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Let me have your name, and I will ask Glinda if she will receive you.” They told who they were, and the girl soldier went into the Castle. After a few moments she came back to say that Dorothy and the others were to be admitted at once.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002214": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002214",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002215": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002215",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002216": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002216",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XXIII<br>\nGlinda The Good Witch Grants Dorothy’s Wish</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002217": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002217",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002218": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002218",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Before they went to see Glinda, however, they were taken to a room of the Castle, where Dorothy washed her face and combed her hair, and the Lion shook the dust out of his mane, and the Scarecrow patted himself into his best shape, and the Woodman polished his tin and oiled his joints.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002219": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002219",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002220": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002220",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>When they were all quite presentable they followed the soldier girl into a big room where the Witch Glinda sat upon a throne of rubies.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002221": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002221",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002222": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002222",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She was both beautiful and young to their eyes. Her hair was a rich red in color and fell in flowing ringlets over her shoulders. Her dress was pure white but her eyes were blue, and they looked kindly upon the little girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002223": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002223",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002224": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002224",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“What can I do for you, my child?” she asked.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002225": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002225",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002226": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002226",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy told the Witch all her story: how the cyclone had brought her to the Land of Oz, how she had found her companions, and of the wonderful adventures they had met with.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002227": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002227",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My greatest wish now,” she added, “is to get back to Kansas, for Aunt Em will surely think something dreadful has happened to me, and that will make her put on mourning; and unless the crops are better this year than they were last, I am sure Uncle Henry cannot afford it.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Glinda leaned forward and kissed the sweet, upturned face of the loving little girl.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Bless your dear heart,” she said, “I am sure I can tell you of a way to get back to Kansas.” Then she added, “But, if I do, you must give me the Golden Cap.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Willingly!” exclaimed Dorothy; “indeed, it is of no use to me now, and when you have it you can command the Winged Monkeys three times.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I think I shall need their service just those three times,” answered Glinda, smiling.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy then gave her the Golden Cap, and the Witch said to the Scarecrow, “What will you do when Dorothy has left us?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“I will return to the Emerald City,” he replied, “for Oz has made me its ruler and the people like me. The only thing that worries me is how to cross the hill of the Hammer-Heads.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“By means of the Golden Cap I shall command the Winged Monkeys to carry you to the gates of the Emerald City,” said Glinda, “for it would be a shame to deprive the people of so wonderful a ruler.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Am I really wonderful?” asked the Scarecrow.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You are unusual,” replied Glinda.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Turning to the Tin Woodman, she asked, “What will become of you when Dorothy leaves this country?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>He leaned on his axe and thought a moment. Then he said, “The Winkies were very kind to me, and wanted me to rule over them after the Wicked Witch died. I am fond of the Winkies, and if I could get back again to the Country of the West, I should like nothing better than to rule over them forever.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My second command to the Winged Monkeys,” said Glinda “will be that they carry you safely to the land of the Winkies. Your brain may not be so large to look at as those of the Scarecrow, but you are really brighter than he is—when you are well polished—and I am sure you will rule the Winkies wisely and well.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Then the Witch looked at the big, shaggy Lion and asked, “When Dorothy has returned to her own home, what will become of you?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Over the hill of the Hammer-Heads,” he answered, “lies a grand old forest, and all the beasts that live there have made me their King. If I could only get back to this forest, I would pass my life very happily there.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My third command to the Winged Monkeys,” said Glinda, “shall be to carry you to your forest. Then, having used up the powers of the Golden Cap, I shall give it to the King of the Monkeys, that he and his band may thereafter be free for evermore.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman and the Lion now thanked the Good Witch earnestly for her kindness; and Dorothy exclaimed:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“You are certainly as good as you are beautiful! But you have not yet told me how to get back to Kansas.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Your Silver Shoes will carry you over the desert,” replied Glinda. “If you had known their power you could have gone back to your Aunt Em the very first day you came to this country.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“But then I should not have had my wonderful brains!” cried the Scarecrow. “I might have passed my whole life in the farmer’s cornfield.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I should not have had my lovely heart,” said the Tin Woodman. “I might have stood and rusted in the forest till the end of the world.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“And I should have lived a coward forever,” declared the Lion, “and no beast in all the forest would have had a good word to say to me.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“This is all true,” said Dorothy, “and I am glad I was of use to these good friends. But now that each of them has had what he most desired, and each is happy in having a kingdom to rule besides, I think I should like to go back to Kansas.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“The Silver Shoes,” said the Good Witch, “have wonderful powers. And one of the most curious things about them is that they can carry you to any place in the world in three steps, and each step will be made in the wink of an eye. All you have to do is to knock the heels together three times and command the shoes to carry you wherever you wish to go.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“If that is so,” said the child joyfully, “I will ask them to carry me back to Kansas at once.”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>She threw her arms around the Lion’s neck and kissed him, patting his big head tenderly. Then she kissed the Tin Woodman, who was weeping in a way most dangerous to his joints. But she hugged the soft, stuffed body of the Scarecrow in her arms instead of kissing his painted face, and found she was crying herself at this sorrowful parting from her loving comrades.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Glinda the Good stepped down from her ruby throne to give the little girl a good-bye kiss, and Dorothy thanked her for all the kindness she had shown to her friends and herself.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy now took Toto up solemnly in her arms, and having said one last good-bye she clapped the heels of her shoes together three times, saying:</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Take me home to Aunt Em!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p class=\"p2\">Instantly she was whirling through the air, so swiftly that all she could see or feel was the wind whistling past her ears.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>The Silver Shoes took but three steps, and then she stopped so suddenly that she rolled over upon the grass several times before she knew where she was.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>At length, however, she sat up and looked about her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“Good gracious!” she cried.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>For she was sitting on the broad Kansas prairie, and just before her was the new farmhouse Uncle Henry built after the cyclone had carried away the old one. Uncle Henry was milking the cows in the barnyard, and Toto had jumped out of her arms and was running toward the barn, barking furiously.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Dorothy stood up and found she was in her stocking-feet. For the Silver Shoes had fallen off in her flight through the air, and were lost forever in the desert.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><h2><a></a>Chapter XXIV<br>\nHome Again</h2></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>Aunt Em had just come out of the house to water the cabbages when she looked up and saw Dorothy running toward her.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“My darling child!” she cried, folding the little girl in her arms and covering her face with kisses. “Where in the world did you come from?”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p>“From the Land of Oz,” said Dorothy gravely. “And here is Toto, too. And oh, Aunt Em! I’m so glad to be at home again!”</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/8b3851c016c3387a/text/000002306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-f3bcb9 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-245572 twpub-8b3851c016c3387a-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
